title: low calorie custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla; stir in milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Contains 79 calories per 1/6 recipe.

title: old-fashioned sour cream drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla. Sift together and stir in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet and bake until delicately browned, just until, when touched with finger, almost no imprint remains.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 425°. Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: tally-ho salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: old-fashioned potato soup
directions: Put the potatoes and onions in a kettle with the salt and cover with cold water (4 cups).
Bring to the boiling point. Cover and cook gently for 20 minutes.
Transfer to a blender and puree the vegetables or simply mash them to a pulp in the water. Add the milk and season to taste with salt and plenty of pepper. Garnish liberally with chopped parsley.

title: beer-batter flounder
directions: In medium bowl, mix beer, flour, cornmeal, parsley, salt and pepper.
In skillet, over medium heat, add 1/2-inch of canola oil. Dip flounder fillets in batter.
Place in hot oil.
Fry until golden (about 3 minutes each), turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: quick fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Cook on low heat until butter is melted.
Remove from heat, add nuts and beat.
Pour in a container that has been buttered.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Cut apple in eight pieces.
Separate crescent rolls.
Peel apples and roll each piece in a crescent roll.
Spray a baking dish with Pam.
Put rolls in dish.
Combine butter, water, sugar, and bring to a boil in a saucepan.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, then add crushed potato chips.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 300° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan candy
directions: Melt chips together over very low heat.
Once melted, add pecans.
With a tablespoon, immediately drop candy one by one onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch flowerets and stems 2 minutes and drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, beaten egg yolks, butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg thoroughly.
Fold in beaten whites.
Pour in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with seeds if desired.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until set at 350°.
Cooks like a souffle but does not fall; remains like a quiche filling.
Freezes very well.

title: healthy banana pudding
directions: Add milk, eggs, vanilla and flour in blender.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2-quart double boiler.
Do not add Equal at this time (it is important that you let it cool as Equal breaks down in heat).
Slice bananas.
Put alternate layers of vanilla wafers and bananas in large serving dish.

title: breakfast sausage egg bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Add soup. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk and pepper, then add to sausage mix. Put in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease well a large paper bag (grocery bag).
Put cleaned whole chicken inside.
May salt and season to taste.
Lay sliced carrots and potatoes around chicken. If preferred, may stuff chicken with your favorite dressing.
Tie paper bag and place in baking pan.
Roast in oven for approximately one hour at 350°. Super easy!
Complete meal in a bag!

title: cocktail wienies
directions: Put sausages in crock-pot and cover with barbecue sauce.
Heat on medium for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Put 6 slices of bacon on top of sausages, then cover with brown sugar.
Simmer at least 2 hours.

title: bourbon pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecan halves.
Place in saucepan and bring to rolling boil on low heat.
Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from stove, add pecans and stir until pecans are well coated and sauce begins to crystallize.
Spread pecans on waxed paper, separate and let cool.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk on top of a double boiler.
Stir mixture until melted.
Combine cake mix, remaining milk and softened margarine.
Blend mixture until cake holds together.
Stir in nuts.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate pieces on top.
Pour melted caramel evenly over top.
Crumble remaining mixture over caramel.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Cover and cook over low heat a few minutes.
Drain pineapple; set fruit aside.
Combine juice, sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, water and soy sauce in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add salt, if desired.
Pour the sauce over the meat and stir in pineapple, green pepper and onion. Simmer until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Serve with white or brown rice.
Serves 4.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Have ready a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine oats, coconut, almonds, sesame seed, sunflower seeds and wheat germ in large mixing bowl. Set aside.
Combine honey and oil. Stir into dry ingredients. Spread in ungreased pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Stir in raisins. Remove to another pan to cool, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 cups.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Serve with Frito chips.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Add meats and mix.
Shape into 1 inch balls. (Can be frozen at this point.)
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes (or longer if frozen).

title: apple pizzas(makes four 6-inch pizzas)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place flour and butter in the bowl; combine until butter disappears.
Add sugar and salt; pour in the cold water.
Blend together with hands.
Knead the dough and then divide into 4 equal pieces.
Roll out pieces and form small circles.
Cut apple slices and put slices on the "pizzas." Sprinkle slices with sugar (1 teaspoon) and cinnamon.
Place pizzas on a cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Mix cold water and corn meal together in top of double boiler. Stir in boiling water and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until it boils. Cover and cook over the boiling water until mush is thickened, about 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serve hot with whole milk.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Roll nuts, candy orange slices and dates in flour.
Add to batter.
Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: santa clara scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
In another bowl, beat sour cream, egg, sugar and lemon peel until well blended.
Add butter to the flour mixture and cut in with a pastry cutter or rub in with fingers until mixture looks like fine granules.
Add prunes and apricots and toss to distribute.
Add sour cream mixture and stir with a spoon until a sticky dough forms.
Drop dough by 1/3 cupfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool, loosely covered with a dish towel, on wire rack.
Makes 10 to 12 scones.

title: hostess peas
directions: Dice bacon and saute until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet. Saute onion in the bacon grease.
Remove onion from skillet.
Put peas, butter, water and lettuce in skillet and cook until lettuce is wilted.
Add bacon and onion.
Heat through and serve.

title: cabbage burger bake
directions: Quarter and shred cabbage (you should have about 8 cups). Spread half in buttered, shallow, 12-cup baking dish.
Saute bacon just until fat starts to cook out in a large frying pan.
Remove; drain and set aside for later.
Stir onion and rice into bacon drippings in frying pan; cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until onion is soft and rice is lightly browned.
Spoon over cabbage in baking dish.
Shape ground beef and pork into 1 large patty in same frying pan.
Brown 5 minutes on each side, then break up into crumbs.
Cook, stirring often, a few minutes longer or until no pink remains.
Spoon over rice mixture in baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cabbage.

title: strawberry sour cream jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water; cool slightly.
Add strawberries (slightly thawed), pineapple (drained) and banana (mashed).
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold and let stand in refrigerator until firm.
Spread with sour cream and put remaining jello on top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: clam chowder soup
directions: Simmer onion, celery and potatoes in small amount of water in a large saucepan until tender.
Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in vegetable mixture.
Add clams.
Cook over low heat until heated through.

title: orange marmalade sauce
directions: Boil 5 minutes	and
chill.
This sauce is delicious on ice cream.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Place cooked beans in casserole.
Add a little liquid from beans. Add undiluted soup.
Place bacon and cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: 4 bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a heavy covered casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: uncle sonny's pasta salad
directions: Mix vegetables, meat and cheese with pasta.
Add Salad Supreme and dressing.
Stir and chill.
Enjoy!

title: kathy's cranberry salsa
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cranberries, sugar, chili powder, lime juice and jalapenos; heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 4 minutes, or until cranberries are tender and mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Stir in scallions and cilantro.
Let stand at room temperature until mixture has cooled.
Enjoy during the holidays with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: broccoli olive linguine
directions: In a large saucepot of boiling, salted water, cook regular and spinach linguine as packages direct.
While linguine is cooking, in a large nonstick skillet, over medium heat, heat oil.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute, until softened.
Add broccoli, pepper flakes and chicken broth.
Cover and cook about 6 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Drain linguine and place in a large serving bowl.
Add broccoli mixture and olives.
Toss well; sprinkle with cheese.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Preboil spareribs about 30 minutes (don't overcook).
Drain and cool.
Line large baking dish or roaster with onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Refrigerate overnight. Cook next day, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: chili-loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into a good-sized loaf.
Spread ketchup on top to taste.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or microwave 15 to 20 minutes on High, turning occasionally.
(Use a round pan for microwave.)

title: siopad
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
When dissolved, add sugar and 2 1/2 cups flour to make a soft sponge.
Beat thoroughly with a wooden spoon.
Set aside to rise until double in bulk (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Add remaining flour and 1/4 cup fat to sponge and mix well.
Turn onto a slightly greased board using remaining 1/4 cup fat and knead until smooth.
Divide dough into 24 to 36 pieces, depending on desired size.
Form into balls; flatten one ball with heel of hand and put filling in the center.
Gather the edges together and seal.
Lay on square piece of paper, sealed side under, and set aside for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce and mix well.

Mix 1 1/2 cans remaining tomato sauce with water, vinegar, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Shape meat mixture into loaf and place on rack in roasting pan. Spoon some sauce over top and place in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done, basting often.
Yields 8 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts and syrup in microwave bowl and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Cook on High for 3 more minutes, then stir well and add margarine and vanilla.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add soda, stirring quickly onto pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Allow to cool and break into pieces.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill for about 2 hours.

title: greek salad
directions: Mound the potato salad on a large platter. Cover the potato salad with the shredded lettuce, then arrange the remaining vegetables in an attractive pattern on the lettuce. Place the anchovies and shrimp on top of the salad. The entire salad is then sprinkled with the vinegar, then the blended oil. Sprinkle liberally with oregano over all and serve at once. Toasted French or Greek bread is served with the salad. Each person serves himself from the beautiful salad platter. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lorna doone
directions: Mix crushed Lorna Doone cookies and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix vanilla pudding, butter pecan ice cream and milk; pour over Lorna Doone mixture.
Let it set in freezer until firm.
Spread container of Cool Whip on top.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Put in freezer 2 or 3 hours, then serve.

title: amish barn soup
directions: Saute together the chopped onions and margarine.
Bring to a boil the water and add bouillon cubes.
Add noodles and cook 3 minutes.
Then add broccoli and salt and cook until tender.
Stir in garlic powder, milk, Velveeta and black pepper.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: onion and sour cream dip
directions: Mix onion soup mix with sour cream just before serving.
Serve with potato chips or crackers of your choice.

title: tangy butter sauce(for cheesy tuna and rice casserole)
directions: Mix all ingredients, heat, and pour over casserole as desired.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in top of double boiler. Beat without cooking for 1 minute. Place over boiling water and cook until stiff peaks form, beating constantly. Remove from boiling water Add vanilla, beat until spreading consistency.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all these ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with 1 package Ritz crackers browned in 1/2 stick margarine.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place one breast at a time between pieces of plastic wrap. Flatten, using flat side of meat mallet and then roll with the rolling pin until 1/8 inch thick.
Peel off wrap.
Flatten other breast the same way.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Divide chives and parsley among the chicken.
Place one slice of cheese and one slice of ham in each piece of chicken.
Roll up chicken: secure with toothpick.
Dip each piece in flour; egg; then bread crumbs.
In medium skillet, heat 1 1/2-2 inches oil to 340°.
Cook chicken in hot oil about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir soup and milk together.
Heat for about 10 minutes.
Pour a tablespoon of the mixture over the chicken.
Garnish with parsley.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths. Shake biscuits in a bag with granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits in a tube pan. Sprinkle chopped nuts between layers.
Melt brown sugar and oleo; boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake in casserole dish covered with foil at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy-do fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, and butter in a large heavy saucepan; heat to boiling. Stir constantly, about 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball stage, (238 degrees); remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients; stir vigorously until will blended. Pour into greased 13 x 3 x 2 inch pan. Cool; cut into squares. Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: frosted pumpkin mousse
directions: Combine all the ingredients and whip until smooth.
Pour into a bowl or 3-cup mold in and freeze.
Allow to soften briefly at room temperature before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lucille stock's poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and poppy seed.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place biscuits in a greased bread pan, layering as necessary.
In a saucepan, bring sugars, cinnamon and margarine to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate.

title: 5 step pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9-inch unbaked pie crust at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
This is good.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: In a bowl, combine the uncooked beef, beans, chili powder and oregano. Spoon into uncooked manicotti shells; arrange in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine water and picante sauce; pour over shells.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; spoon sour cream over top.
Sprinkle with cheese, onions and olives if desired.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yields 8 servings.

title: marie's invention
directions: Brown sausage, hamburger, and garlic.
Drain.
In a separate pan, add tomatoes, salt/pepper, celery seed and oregano.
Leave on until hot.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, stirring until cheese melts. Cook noodles as directed.
Mix meat into sauce.
Layer in pan, alternating layers of sauce and noodles.
Bake 350° until hot. Garnish with parmesan cheese.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
In medium saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Remove from heat; stir in tuna and pimento. Prepare noodles as label directs (drain).
Combine noodles and tuna mixture in casserole.
Bake 25 minutes; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes more until bubbly.

title: salmon loaf mousse
directions: Clean and flake salmon.
Add well beaten egg yolks and remaining ingredients in order (except egg whites).
Mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites gently into salmon mixture.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-cup 10-inch tube pan.
In sifter, mix flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt. Sift into large bowl.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternately beat in flour mixture in fourths and milk in thirds, beginning with flour.
Beat in grated chocolate and vanilla extract.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer as follows:
noodles, beef, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour all ingredients into large pan on top of stove.
Cook over medium heat until red hots are melted.
Stir often so red hots won't stick to bottom of pan.
Serve hot.

title: fat-free fancy fried rice
directions: Pour eggs into nonstick skillet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Cook until set in 1 large pancake.
Remove from pan, cool and cut into thin strips; reserve.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Put almond bark in 200° oven and melt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: the best two-crusted apple pie in new england("apple country pie")
directions: Whip into loose meringue, dribble over pie.
Bake at 350 degrees approx. 1 hour.
Let cool 1 hour before serving.

title: tomato soup
directions: Core tomatoes and mash up.
Cook tomatoes, celery, onions and red pepper until tender.
Put through sieve and add remaining ingredients; seal.

title: green bean-corn casserole
directions: Place drained green beans and corn in 9 x 9-inch dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion; spread on top of vegetables. Melt oleo; mix in almonds and crackers.
Pour on top of cheese soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour; microwave for 2 to 3 minutes before baking to cook onion.

title: apple stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cinnamon.

title: e-z chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta.
Blend other ingredients in pasta and mix all together. Sliced olives are a good addition.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: carrot and pecan cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder in bowl.
Add to egg mixture; beat well.
Add carrots gradually, mixing well.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake. Garnish with additional pecans.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: orange upside-down cake(6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grate 1 tablespoon of colored zest from oranges.
Peel oranges, cutting away all white pith right down to the flesh.
Cut sections away from membrane.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and brown sugar in a 9-inch cake pan.
Arrange orange sections in sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat remaining 8 tablespoons butter and granulated sugar until fluffy. Beat in zest, eggs and vanilla.
Beat in half the flour, then milk and finally remaining flour.
Spread over oranges.
Bake until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes; turn onto a platter.
Leave 1 minute before removing pan.

title: drop mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Pour 2/3 full in greased muffin pan after mixing ingredients well.
Cook approximately 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6 biscuits. Double recipe to make 12.

title: ms. diane's pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice.
Put in large enamel pot and add pickling lime and cold water.
Soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash all remaining lime from pickles.
Soak for 3 hours in ice water. Drain good and then add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Tie up pickling spices and cloves or use a tea bag holder.
(This prevents them from being next to the pickles, which causes discoloration.)
Soak overnight.
Bring to a boil and cook for 30 minutes.
Put in warm jars and seal.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a bowl; add pudding and Tang.
Mix well.
Toss with fruit.

title: tofu sandwich filling
directions: Drain liquid from tofu.
Mash tofu and add chopped carrots, onion, celery and olives.
Mix together and add salad dressing or mayonnaise to desired texture.
Add garlic powder to desired taste.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: If whipping cream is used, whip according to directions on package or substitute the Cool Whip for the whipping cream.
Fold fruit into mayonnaise.

title: filled cookie dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together, cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Use flour to roll and cut in circles, fill and cover with another circle; crimp edges to seal.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix first 4 items together.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a bowl to congeal.

title: german meatballs
directions: Mix beef and next 9 ingredients.
Roll in 2-inch balls.
Brown in oil.
Drain.
Add soup and bouillon.
Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve on noodles.

title: baked spinach
directions: Combine all and bake in greased baking dish.
Set the dish in pan of water while baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bachelor's stew
directions: Season stew meat as desired.
Put meat in a bag with flour and shake until well coated.
Brown meat in oil; drain excess.
Add mushroom soup and package of dry mix plus 1 soup can of water. Simmer on low to medium heat, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Great over wide egg noodles or rice.

title: dressing
directions: Heat soup and giblet water.
Pour over all the other ingredients and mix.

title: curried chicken bake(low-cal)
directions: In a small saucepan, melt margarine and add remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Cook, stirring until sauce thickens. Spray a small baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place chicken in a single layer. Brush with curry mixture. Bake in a 375° oven until brown and cooked, 35 to 40 minutes, basting with pan juices every 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together except cheese and chips.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish and cover with cheese and chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: economical punch
directions: Mix sugar and hot water until sugar is melted, then add lemon juice, pineapple and grapefruit juice and 6 cups cold water. Refrigerate.
Punch is better if made the day before using.
When ready to serve, add lime sherbet (1 quart per bowl) and ginger ale slowly.
Have everything cold.
Do not add ice cubes.
Makes enough for two punch bowls.

title: cranberry quencher
directions: Combine cranberry-apple and pineapple juices in a large container or punch bowl. Stir in lemonade concentrate. Garnish glasses with pineapple, cranberries and/or mint if desired. Yields 6 quarts.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Stir until dissolved over boiling water.
Pour warm mixture into whipped cream.
Add defrosted strawberries and nuts.
Crush wafers.
Put a light coat of the crumbs in bottom of 2 ice cube trays.
Pour in strawberry mixture.
Cover the tops with more crumbs.
Cover with waxed paper or Saran Wrap and allow to stand overnight in freezer. (This keeps indefinitely in freezer.)

title: smoked chicken
directions: Soak chickens overnight in water, pickling salt, onion powder, black pepper, lemon, maple flavoring and bay leaf.
Rub on and in chickens brown sugar, onion or garlic powder and black pepper, then smoke.

title: good punch
directions: Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and canned cream over low-medium heat, stirring constantly, until it starts to boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir, stir and stir.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Makes 6 pounds.
Stir entire time; will scorch easily. Won't harden if rainy!

title: fish dish for 2
directions: Serving Suggestions:
Serve with salad, corn on the cob, dinner rolls.

title: 5 layer dinner
directions: First, you hard-cook some eggs (more than one for each person).
Use 3 for 2, 5 for 3 and so on, depending on how many eggs you have on hand, how hungry you are and maybe on how expensive eggs are at the time.
Take the shells off the cooked eggs, cut the whites into smallish pieces and mash the yolks in a separate dish.
Keep them warm.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute shrimp and shallots in butter and oil.
Add garlic when you turn shrimp (turn shrimp when they are pink halfway through). Serve as is or on top of pasta.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Form in small balls or use a dipper. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Do not press balls down.
They will spread.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; slice thin.
Chop onions and green peppers. Combine with cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.

title: rosemary walnuts
directions: Melt butter; add next 3 ingredients.
Pour over walnuts, stir to coat.
Place nuts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Be careful not to burn.)

title: wassail drink
directions: Boil water and steep tea bags for 10 minutes.
Discard tea bags and combine remaining ingredients.
Boil and serve warm. Very nice at Christmastime.

title: homemade hummus
directions: Soak beans in 6 cups water overnight, then rinse well.
Drain. Place beans in crock-pot (high) for 10 to 12 hours until quite soft.
Cook also with 3 cloves of the garlic, 5 cups of water, onion and Mexican seasoning mix.
When done, place beans in food processor (use a slotted spoon so most of broth is left in crock-pot).
Blend with lemon, remaining 3 cloves garlic, white miso, olive oil, cayenne and tahini.
Add more broth little by little as needed to make a smooth paste.
You can find miso and tahini at health food markets.
This makes great sandwiches with mayo, avocado, sprouts and grated carrots.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in medium-large saucepan.
Bring to a boil until slow rolling boil is maintained for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Place popped popcorn in large roaster pan. Slowly drizzle syrup over popcorn (and peanuts, if chosen).
Bake in slow oven at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Stir the mixture every 15 minutes through baking time.)
Cool and enjoy!

title: cheese fondue
directions: Rub saucepan with garlic, then discard clove.
Heat wine, adding cheese slowly.
When cheese melts, add Kirsch.
Stir in figure 8 pattern.
Add cornstarch.
Stir until thickened.
Serve with cubed French bread.

title: uncle  thanksgiving dressing
directions: Fry onion, celery, peppers and olives in a liberal amount of shortening--Mom uses butter--until celery is rather soft.
Season with salt and pepper.
Crumble bread and pour drippings from the bird on bread.
Mom uses chicken bouillon cubes.
Add mixture and mix.
Moisten well and season to taste.
Place in oven in greased baking dish 'till browned.
350 degrees about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Add 3 cups of hot water to large boiler.
Place 6 to 8 noodles in boiling water with teaspoon of butter.
Cook approximately 20 to 25 minutes and drain.
While noodles cook, brown ground beef; drain well.
Add sauce to ground beef and simmer 10 minutes.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve salt and sugar with jello and boiling water.
Stir cream and mayo into cooled jello.
Add mashed cottage cheese and all other ingredients.
May add pimento or small amount of red pepper for color.
If doubling recipe, use less mayonnaise.

title: summer salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in oleo.
Put cooked rice into a mixing bowl; add all ingredients and mix.

title: mama's strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring often.
Bake pie crust as directed.
Slice strawberries into crust.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Delicious!

title: barbecued chicken with glaze
directions: In large, screw-top jar, combine tomato sauce, olive oil, orange juice, vinegar, oregano, salt, peppercorns and garlic. Cover and shake vigorously to blend.

title: snickers brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir into sugar mixture.
Fold in chopped Snickers.
Spoon into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with chopped Hershey bars.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 2 dozen squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Mix until smooth and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes or until mixture is clear and thick. Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Put while hot over berries. Pour into baked pie shell; chill until set.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all filling ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mashed potatoes(kid's stuff)
directions: Get a bowl of hot water on stove and then put macaroni in and wait until it starts boiling on 9°.
Put cheese in and stir before it boils then get macaroni out and enjoy.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Form dough into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease pizza pan.
Mix pizza crust mix together according to directions.
Cook ground beef and drain. Spread dough in pizza pan.
Add sauce, meat, cheese and any other topping you may like.
Finally you fold outside of pizza into middle.
Place in oven for 30 minutes or until middle is done.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into large pieces; soak in 2 gallons of water and 2 cups of household lime for 24 hours.
Wash in clear water and then soak in clear water for 4 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients and let cucumbers stand in this mixture overnight. Then boil hard for 40 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and process for 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet from rice mix and hot water; place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside. Sprinkle pork chops with pepper and place over rice mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Combine soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Sprinkle chicken tenders (or any part of chicken) with Creole seasoning.
Brown in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove and set aside. In same skillet, brown sausage and vegetables until vegetables are tender.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Combine the cooked Rice-A-Roni and sausage mixture.
Add the Mexicorn and the soups.
Stir in 1 cup of cheese.
Pour this mixture into a casserole dish.
Place the chicken pieces on top of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small strips.
Brown in	grease	or oil. Add to	steak
the onion and green pepper,
also
in
strips. Brown with
steak.
Turn skillet down to 300°
and
add
beef broth and onion soup mix.
Let simmer until
steak
is tender, approximately 30 minutes.
If desired, thicken steak and broth mixture.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine egg, confectioners sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers; cover with sliced bananas.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Spread layer of crushed pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Cool until firm.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; crumble bread in bottom of baking dish.
Beat other ingredients together; pour over bread and sausage.
Put grated cheese on top of mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Great for brunch.

title: easy crab asparagus pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate. Layer crabmeat, asparagus and onion in prepared pie plate.
Top with cheeses.
Season with pepper.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter.
Add milk and eggs; stir until blended. Pour over vegetables and cheeses.
Bake about 30 minutes or until filling is puffed and knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated roast(sirloin)
directions: Combine all ingredients except roast.
Makes enough to marinate about 4 pounds of meat.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature.
If you run out of sauce to cover while cooking, use Wish-Bone garlic dressing. Cook roast on grill 20 minutes per pound.
Keep basting with marinade sauce while cooking.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine fat, beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until beef is brown; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Turn into 8-inch square (1 1/2-quart) casserole dish.
Cut cheese into strips; spread over meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are brown.

title: lemon gelatin cake
directions: Combine mixes, oil and water.
Beat 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry beef, garlic, sugar and salt in hot oil.
Stir in sake and soy sauce; cook, covered, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove meat and set aside.
Add broccoli and 3/4 cup water to skillet (or wok).
Bring to boiling; stir and then cook, covered, 2 to 5 minutes more.
Add meat.
Combine cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into center of mixture.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until thick and bubbly.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pour over chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan and marinate for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for first hour, then uncover last half hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Cook squash and onions together.
Add butter.
Mix in pimento, soup, sour cream and stuffing mix, reserving enough stuffing mix to garnish top.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients except pecans and chocolate chips.
When other ingredients are mixed well, add pecans and chocolate chips and blend with a spoon.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If you double the recipe, it will make 3 pies.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a well-greased pan for 35 minutes at 400°.
Freezes well.

title: honey b's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet or large round pan (10 to 12 inches).
Stir in brown sugar until it melts.
Remove from fire. Add drained pineapple slices (reserve juice) and arrange with cherries and pecan halves.
Mix cake batter according to directions substituting pineapple juice for water.
Pour over mixture in pan and bake according to cake mix directions.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Turn upside down on serving plate.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, mandarin oranges with juice and cooking oil. Bake 3 layers for 25 minutes at 350°; cool layers. Frost with a mixture of pineapple, pudding mix and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown beef, onions, pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients, simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan balls(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Work in flour.
The last bit of flour may be worked in with hands.
Add nuts.
Chill dough.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cream together until smooth.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Chill dough; roll into balls about the size of a quarter.
Place on cookie sheet; flatten with a fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross design.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: deanna's pina colada cake
directions: Mix white cake mix by directions, adding 1 cup coconut to cake mix.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan with chopped nuts. Pour cake mixture over nuts and bake per directions on cake box. Take baked cake from oven.
While slightly warm, poke deep holes all over cake.
Pour 1 can Coco Lopez into all the cake holes, then pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk into cake holes.
Separate cake from edge of pan with knife and add both milk and Coco Lopez here as well.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
When completely cooled, cover with Cool Whip.
Cake is best served after it has been refrigerated for 2 to 3 hours.

title: creamy noodles and rice
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook carrots and onion until tender, stirring often.
Add water, soup mix and rice.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in dish.
Mix cheese, sugar and flour.
Spread over pineapple.
Cover with melted margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs. Bake 20 minutes at 350° or 325°.

title: popey biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with butter.
Bake at 450°.
Makes 31 biscuits.

title: glenn's cabbage stuff(stew)
directions: Cube potatoes.
Cut cabbage; slice onions.
Saute onions in margarine until clear.
Brown cubed meat and add to onions.
Add cubed potatoes and cut cabbage.
Steam all together.
Add dried red peppers last for crispiness.
Season as desired.
When using smoked sausage, no other seasoning should be needed.
Cooks in about 30 to 40 minutes (1 dish meal).
Serve with bread sticks.

title: crab and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in Dutch oven or other ovenproof container.
Saute celery, onion, carrot, mushrooms and green pepper until onion is transparent.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: 6 layer casserole
directions: Grease 2 quart casserole dish, layer as above and bake 3 hours at 300 degrees.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute for 3 minutes in 3 tablespoons butter, onion, celery and green peppers.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and cover with crushed crackers that have been mixed with the 1/2 cup oleo.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Combine beef with flour and brown slightly in fat.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Put into an 8 or 9-inch square pan and top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: passover cheesecake
directions: To make crust, press macaroons on bottom and sides of a greased spring-form pan.
Set aside until ready to fill with batter.

title: honey pork oriental
directions: Cut the pork into 1-inch squares.
Brown the pork in 2 tablespoons oil, stirring frequently, for 15 minutes.
Combine 1 envelope brown gravy mix, 3/4 cup water, 1/4 cup honey, the soy sauce, red wine vinegar, ginger and garlic salt.
Add to the skillet.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add carrots and cook for 15 minutes more.
Add the green pepper and onion; cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
(Very sweet and tender.)

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix
first
4 ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Put Ritz crackers on top and melted margarine on top of crackers. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: delicious zucchini
directions: Place zucchini slices in a buttered, oblong casserole dish. Place tomatoes, green pepper and onion between zucchini slices. Sprinkle salt, Beau Monde seasoning, pepper, cheese and sugar on top.
Drizzle butter evenly over the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oreo cookies pudding cake
directions: Mix together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, flour and sugar, mixing well.
Dip bread into mixture, coating both sides.
Cook on griddle until brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup or powdered sugar.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and egg; pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Put marshmallows over crust.
Mix peanut butter chips, syrup and 1/4 cup margarine together and microwave 2 minutes.
Pour over marshmallows.
Press in salted peanuts.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Use as much of the ingredients as desired.

title: chocolate unbaked cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook until butter melts and bring to a rolling boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Spoon on wax paper.
Nuts may be added.

title: simple strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Combine flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, sugar, gelatin and buttermilk; stir vigorously until well-blended.
Add flour mixture and blend well.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with mixer as directed.
Fold in Cool Whip. Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bottom with a layer of graham crackers.
Add a layer of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Add the rest of the pudding mixture.
Add a final layer of graham crackers on top.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple and sugar.
Spread over brownie. Spread strawberries and bananas over pizza.
Sprinkle with nuts and drizzle chocolate topping over pizza.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and combine with tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Add to noodles.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with almonds.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In a 3 qt microwave safe bowl, cook sugar, syrup and hot water for 12 minutes and 30 seconds on high until a fine thread is formed when dripping mixture from a spoon.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl.
Fix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Combine both mixtures in a large bowl and beat for 3 to 4 minutes, adding vanilla.
Put cream mixture in crust.
Top with pie filling and let chill before serving.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Make chocolate cake according to directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Crumble cake with a fork.
Make pudding according to directions.
Thaw Cool Whip.
Crush candy bars.
Layer in trifle bowl or other tall glass container 1/2 of cake mix, 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the crumbled candy bars. Repeat another layer with other half of ingredients.

title: condensed milk
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Can be used in all recipes calling for condensed milk

title: mike's fried turkey
directions: Prepare the turkey as for baking.
Do not fry the heart, liver or gizzard as they become too hard to eat.
Chop the bell peppers into small pieces.
Put them in a blender with 3 tablespoons of water and liquify.
Melt the butter and oleo in a saucepan. Strain the liquified bell peppers through a fine strainer or a paper towel into the pan with melted butter and oleo.
Strain the Italian dressing like the peppers into the pan.
Add the 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon mustard, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce and the bottle of onion juice to the pan.
Bring the mixture to a slight boil.
Let cool a bit (until you can handle).

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While still
warm, pierce cake every 1 1/2 inches with wooden spoon handle.
Boil
sugar
and
milk
together for 1 minute. Pour
in holes
and	over cake.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle thawed coconut on top.
Chill overnight.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic.
Fry about 5 more minutes.
Remove pan from direct heat and slowly stir in flour. Add parsley, bay leaves, salt, cayenne and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked, fluffy rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook,
cool and drain broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients. Fold in broccoli.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice dish
directions: Arrange in layers, in the order given, in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Mash bananas with a fork and add lemon juice.
Cream shortening and sugar well, until light.
Add sifted ingredients and milk alternately.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mom's doughnuts
directions: Mix together.
Fry in oil.
Glaze with mixture of powdered sugar and water.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese and Miracle Whip until creamed.
Then mix in bacon, Parmesan and onion.

title: italian breaded round steak
directions: Take round steak, put in egg and milk mixture and let soak for a while.
Put bread crumbs on paper or plate.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Put cut pieces of steak into bread crumb mixture, about one teaspoon each of seasoning.
After breading, let dry for 15 minutes.
Heat skillet; add 1/4 cup of oil to hot pan.
Cook on medium until preferred doneness.
Very good.

title: chewy charlies
directions: Mix margarine, canned milk, sugar and cocoa in saucepan and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper to cool.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Core apples and cut into bite sizes.
Combine apples chunks with Cool Whip, slivers of Snickers bars and drained crushed pineapple.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes many servings.

title: chocolate cherry cheese cake
directions: If you have Tiara pans, cook in them.
If using regular layer cake pans, cut out circle 1-inch in from the edge of cake layer and at least 1/2-inch deep.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Blend oil and vinegar.
Add salt, garlic salt and pepper. Stir.
Mix with olives, green chiles, tomatoes, onions anad avocados.
Chill for several hours for flavors to mix.
Serve cold with tortilla chips.
Very good!

title: holiday popcorn
directions: Toss together popcorn, nuts, apricots and raisins.
Blend syrup, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over popcorn mix; toss lightly until evenly coated.
Put on buttered jelly roll pan.
Heat in 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Prick bottom of pastry with fork.
Bake in 450° oven 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Layer 1/2 the broccoli over Parmesan cheese.
Continue with layers of 1/2 Swiss cheese and onions; repeat with remaining broccoli, Swiss cheese and onions. Beat eggs.
Add chicken broth, cream, salt and Tabasco; mix well. Pour over broccoli mixture in pastry shell.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325°; bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in cream.
Add all ingredients to cream mixture.
Pack in cracker box (lined with wax paper) and chill.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread; add salt, pepper, onion, tomatoes, green pepper, celery and bacon.
Add only enough dressing to moisten. This recipe is good with most everything, but especially good with beans and vegetables.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Can be baked in an iron skillet.
Place 1 tablespoon of oil in skillet and heat. Then pour in corn bread mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: canadian cheddar cheese soup(serves 4)
directions: Melt the butter in a 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat. Reduce the heat to low; add the onion and carrot and cook, covered, for about 5 minutes or until the onion is soft.
Stir in the flour and cook 3 or 4 more minutes.
Gradually add the chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Stir in the mustard and paprika.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars, blend.
Add beaten egg, then dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 60 small cookies.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix salt with cabbage; let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess water.
Add carrot, pepper and celery.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Put all ingredients except water in a bowl.
Mix two minutes. Add hot water and beat two minutes more.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Or pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast; bone and tear into small bite-size pieces (set aside).
Set aside 2 cups of chicken broth.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine; coat the croutons of stuffing mix with the melted margarine.
Divide in one-half; set aside.
Add the vegetable seasoning packet to 1/2 cup chicken broth and boil 5 minutes; set aside.
Blend together the cream of chicken soup and sour cream (do not beat).
Set aside.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Mix pudding, sugar, milk and margarine together in a medium heavy saucepan.
Stir until smooth.
Cook and stir to a rolling boil.
Boil an additional 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Beat until candy loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered pan. When cooled and hardened, cut into squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, line with heavy-duty foil, leaving enough foil in center to seal.
Place pork chops in bottom of pan. Pour cream of mushroom soup over the pork chops; sprinkle with salt and pepper and pour water over soup.
Cut margarine into small pieces and place on top of the soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and seal.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: burger beans
directions: Lightly fry onion and pepper in small amount of cooking oil. Stir in ground beef and cook until meat loses red color.
Mix with other ingredients and bake for 30 minutes or until light brown on top in 375° oven.

title: norma's chicken casserole
directions: Put broccoli in baking dish.
Place chicken over broccoli. Mix mayonnaise, curry, soup and cream.
Pour over chicken.
Add cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.

title: jessie cakes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar when melted.
Do not cook.
Stir in sugar well.
Take off stove burner; add well beaten eggs, stirred in lightly.
Then add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Raise once; shape (two hours first, one hour second).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: philadelphia cream cheese kolachy(a bohemian cookie)
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder. Mix thoroughly.
Roll out thin and cut with small glass.
Fill center with solo filling.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes to a light brown.

title: granny's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut.

title: banana-nut salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add egg; mix thoroughly.
Add butter, vinegar and water; mix thoroughly.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Dip bananas in cool dressing and roll in nuts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage balls(appetizer)
directions: Let sausage get to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with hands until it is all mixed thoroughly.
Roll into bite-size balls.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
After freezing, put in plastic bags.
Can be kept in freezer indefinitely.
When ready to use, take from freezer and place on cookie sheet.
Cook immediately in 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons into 1/8-inch of hot oil.
Flatten patties to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cook until golden brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix and let set at least 12 hours.
Then add:

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, eggs, vanilla, brown sugar and sugar.
Then add sifted flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
When all mixed together, put uncooked oatmeal in.
Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie filling
directions: Scatter pecan halves in prepared tart shell.
Bring sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and finely-cut chocolate.
Beat eggs.
Pour syrup mixture slowly into eggs, whipping constantly.
Pour filling over pecans, making sure that they are well-covered with filling.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, until filling is set, and a table knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: spicy mayhaw chicken drummettes
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Combine soup, dressing and jelly; mix well.
Heat to melt jelly.
Place chicken pieces in uncovered baking dish; spoon sauce over chicken pieces.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
(The remaining sauce can be kept refrigerated for about 2 weeks.)

title: deep dish pan pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain well. Add pizza sauce from box, tomatoes and optional ingredients. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix pizza dough according to directions on box.
Add a little more flour and vegetable oil to make more.
Put in a 10 x 13-inch pan; bring dough up on sides. Pour hamburger mixture on dough.
Add grated cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together in a big mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients except chips; mix well.
Add
chocolate chips to batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: crispy scallop potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat 1-quart casserole with vegetable spray.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: fruit cookie pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookies on an ungreased pizza pan and bake according to instructions on back of cookie package until done. Let cool.
In medium bowl, stir cream cheese with spoon or use mixer to eliminate lumps; add strawberry yogurt and mix until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cool cookie pizza. Cover with fruit.
Just before serving, spray whipped topping on. Enjoy!
It's so-o-o good and easy.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and combine the two mixtures.
Flour raisins and nut meats.
Add to the above mixture.
Pour into layer pans and bake in slow oven (300°) for about 1 hour or until cake leaves side of pan clean.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: dynamites
directions: Mix meat, eggs and bread crumbs together.
Form into hot dog shape.
Dice peppers, onions and celery.
Coat bottom of pan with small amount of oil.
Add onions to meat and brown.
Add all, except tomato juice, into slow cooker.
Add just enough juice to cover.
Add red pepper sauce to taste (hot or mild).
Let simmer in slow cooker for 5 to 6 hours.
Makes large batch.
Can freeze. Serve in hot dog rolls or over rice.

title: easy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Set aside 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Stir together remaining dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Press crust mixture lightly into bottom and three-quarters of the way up the sides of a greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch or spring-loaded round).

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Add together in blender and blend for 30 seconds.
Pour over apples.
Top with streusel.

title: milk frappe
directions: In blender, mix all ingredients until liquid is thick and foamy.

title: buttermilk dinner rolls
directions: Mix all well except flour. Add flour one cup at a time until you have a very stiff dough. Place into a large bowl and let rise until doubled. Punch down and let rise the second time. After second rise, make into rolls; place into a well oiled baking pan. Let rise until almost doubled. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: world's greatest cookies
directions: Cream margarine, butter and sugars until creamy. Add egg and oil, mixing well. Gradually add flour, salt and baking soda. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix and shape into ball.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine water, 1/4 cup salsa, margarine and stuffing.
Mix well and place in 2-quart saucepan.
Arrange chicken on top of stuffing.
Pour remaining salsa on meat.
Loosely cover dish. Cook in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sauce for basting
directions: Sprinkle chicken generously with garlic salt; set on rack in foil-lined, shallow baking pan.
Baste chicken with sauce.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Turn and baste during baking.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients and pour over orange sherbet. Serves 50.

title: school day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in a 375° oven until bubbly, approximately 25 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add rest and form into 2-inch thick rolls, rolled in flour and then in wax paper.
Place in flat dish and then in refrigerator overnight or freezer.
Slice thin and bake on greased sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Sift dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add chocolate to hot mashed potatoes.
Add to sugar, eggs and margarine mixture.
Then add dry ingredients and milk.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 375° oven.
Frost as desired.

title: coconut-pineapple spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in coconut and preserves.
Cover and refrigerate. Yield: 1 1/4 cups.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Work mayonnaise and sugar together with a spoon until smooth.
Add water and vanilla to dry ingredients. Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth.
Turn into greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: carolyn's picadillo(heart healthy)
directions: Unusual flavors make this tortilla filling a winner!

title: texas gold bars
directions: Mix the first four ingredients well.
Pat in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the last three ingredients well; pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
This will melt in your mouth.

title: vanilla pie pudding
directions: Melt butter and add milk and the sugar.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients with a wire whisk until smooth.
I then use a spoon, stirring constantly until thick.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Cover the cherries, pineapple, nuts and marshmallow with mayonnaise.
Then mix according to package directions.
Mix Dream Whip and fold into fruit mixture.
Freeze overnight in a 9 x 13-inch Tupperware container.

title: brandied cranberry sauce
directions: Pour the fresh, cleaned cranberries into a shallow 9 x 13-inch pan in a single layer.
Sprinkle 2 cups sugar over the berries; do not stir.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool to room temperature.
Uncover and pour the brandy or cognac over berries.
Sprinkle an additional 1/2 cup sugar over all and stir well.
(Eliminate 1/2 cup sugar if you prefer it tart.) This keeps in the refrigerator "forever."

title: peek-a-boo coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla, baking powder and flour.
Mix well.
Spread 2/3 batter in 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, which is greased and floured.
Spread entire can of fruit filling over batter.
Drop by tablespoons the remaining batter.
Some filling will show between spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar after cool.

title: banana raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine in bowl bananas, egg, milk, oil and cereal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Spoon into greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg in bowl; mix well.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, 3/4 cup water and chocolate in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Using mixer, stir in flour, 2 cups sugar, 2 eggs, sour cream, soda and salt. Pour into well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate mixture.
Swirl into batter with knife.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes with vegetable brush under running water until clean.
Boil whole with skins on until tender.
Let cool. Remove skins and slice potato.

title: mom's chile con queso(dip or spread)
directions: Cook cheese in double boiler; melt, stirring occasionally. Mixture thickens as it heats.
Mix in sauce and chiles.
Let sit for several minutes.
Serve hot with restaurant style chips.

title: pumpkin cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast; set aside.
In a small pan, heat and stir pumpkin, milk, sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and salt until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to flour-yeast, along with egg.
Beat on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on high for 3 minutes. Stir in enough flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Knead about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Roll into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil mixture of the first 5 ingredients
for about 5 minutes. Add the soda; stir well.
Pour over popcorn which has been popped. Bake for 1 hour at 250°; stir every 15 minutes.
(Easiest to bake in a large roaster.)

title: berry trifle
directions: About 4 hours before serving, mix in bowl the cream cheese, milk, sugar and vanilla extract until smooth.
Then fold in the Cool Whip.
Separate ladyfingers into individual cookies.
Mix orange juice and liqueur.
Drizzle over ladyfingers to moisten.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Grease a large glass pan; layer bottom with croutons.
Top with crumbled sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; pour over croutons, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cake is done, poke holes in top of cake.
While still hot, pour topping over cake.
Let cool and serve.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine the egg and milk.
In a shallow dish, combine the crackers, thyme, paprika and pepper.
Set aside.
Skin chicken and wash.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Dip chicken pieces, one at a time, in egg mixture, then roll in cracker mixture.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: Place sugar, Karo, salt and pecans in a microwave-safe bowl. Stir.
Microwave 4 minutes.
Remove bowl.
Stir again, then microwave 4 additional minutes.
Remove bowl.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave. Add baking soda.
Pour contents onto buttered piece of aluminum foil. Cool about 30 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine water and Eagle Brand, stirring until well blended.
Add pudding; beat until well blended.
Chill for at least 5 minutes.
Slice bananas and allow to stand in lemon juice while pudding is chilling.
Once the pudding has set, fold in whipped cream until well blended.
In a glass bowl, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.
End with pudding.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chop vegetables.
Mix with peas (uncooked).
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and set overnight.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Mix apples with brown sugar to taste.
Cover with cake mix. Melt and pour margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with crushed pecans.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: california cake cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cornbread using all the liquid and egg called for if using a mix.
Mix ingredients for cake using all the liquid and egg called for.
Combine batter in a large mixing bowl and beat with hand mixer until smooth.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix pineapple juice, ketchup, cornstarch and set aside.
Cook water and sugar on medium heat until melted, reduce heat then add pineapple juice; stir well until thick.
Serve when eggrolls are still hot.

title: see's fudge
directions: Combine the first four ingredients in a bowl.
Combine the remaining ingredients in medium saucepan; stir mixture until boils. Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over mixture in bowl.
Stir until chocolate and butter melt.
Pour into a greased, square cake pan.
Place in fridge to harden.

title: meredith's chicken
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with sliced dried beef.
Wrap each half breast with 1 slice bacon.
Place on dried beef.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Can be made ahead and baked 2 hours at 250°.)

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Add all other ingredients and mix. Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2-inch crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 35 minutes

title: 15 minute chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, nuts, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and 1 cup of potato chips. Put in casserole. Put remaining chips on top. Pour on soup and egg slices. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix unsweetened chocolate, sugar, butter and milk together in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1-quart glass container, combine sugar and corn syrup and stir.
Cook on high 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir well. Cook on high for an additional 3 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, stirring well.
Cook on high 1 minute.
Add baking soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture immediately onto buttered cookiesheet.
Spread thinly.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: caramelized onions
directions: In medium skillet, heat margarine or butter over medium-low heat until melted.
Add onion.
Cover and cook on medium-low heat until onion is tender, about 13 to 15 minutes.
Uncover; add sugar. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until onion is golden, stirring constantly, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot over burgers, prime ribs or beef steaks.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot and cold water.
Cool until it begins to gel.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Gel until thick. Mix, cook and cool pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Spread on top of thickened Jell-O.
Mix softened cream cheese and whipped topping.
Spread on top of salad.
Garnish with coconut or nuts.

title: liver and potato casserole
directions: Cut
liver into 1 inch pieces;	flour, salt and pepper. Fry until
done.
Fry
potatoes
and onion until tender.
Mix soup with
milk.
Mix
liver and potatoes together in a large baking dish.
Pour
soup
mixture	over and bake at 350° until hot.

title: vegetable potato soup
directions: Saute bacon until light brown and crisp.
Drain and set aside. Saute onion in drippings until golden.
Combine stock, onion and bacon in soup kettle.
Add vegetables and potatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Season to taste.
Heat onion rings under broiler.
Use onion rings as garnish.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole(april, 1995)
directions: Heat oil; saute onion over medium heat.
Add hamburger and brown.
Stir in roni and tomatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter with graham cracker crumbs.
Press down. Beat eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks butter; mix 15 minutes. Pour over crust.
Slice bananas all over mixture.
Add pineapple and cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Sift ingredients together; mix until crumbly.
Add egg and blend well.
Spread more than half on cookie sheet.
Place fruit filling on top of flour mixture.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Apple juice and ginger ale should be chilled.
Thaw orange juice and lemonade.
Mix all ingredients, ginger ale last, and serve.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
In large bowl, mix sugar and spices except nutmeg.
Add pumpkin, milk, eggs to sugar and spice mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until firm, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black beans and rice salad
directions: Combine the rice, beans, tomatoes, cheese (if desired) and parsley in large bowl.
In a cup, whisk the dressing and lime juice; pour over the rice mixture; toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce. Serves 4.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Mix in ice cream until completely melted.
Chill until almost set.
Stir in strawberries.

title: jam bars
directions: Grease 8 or 9-inch micro-safe dish.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add all but jam and blend well.
Press one-half mixture into dish.
Micro 4 minutes.
Spread jam over baked mixture. Crumble rest of mix over jam and press lightly.
Micro an additional 6 minutes.
Cool and cut into small bars (32).

title: sour cream baked chicken
directions: Spray a baking pan with Pam.
Place one piece of chicken in palm of hand and spread evenly with sour cream.
Place each piece in pan, one at a time, with sides touching (sour cream on bottom). When all pieces of chicken are in pan, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread remaining sour cream over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours for sour cream to tenderize chicken.
To bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chicken with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve with rice, a green vegetable and salad.

title: cooky-jar gingersnaps
directions: Measure flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt into sifter. Cream shortening until soft in medium size bowl.
Gradually add sugar, creaming after each addition, until mixture is fluffy. Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture; blend well.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Put meat in bottom of baking dish or dutch oven.
Layer vegetables on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the top.
Spread both cans of soup over the top.
Cover.
Bake 5 hours at 250° if using frozen meat.
Bake 5 hours at 300° if using thawed meat.

title: italian cookie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter or oleo.
Add well-beaten eggs.
Add Ricotta cheese and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Do not make dough stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (approximately 12 minutes).

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of a pizza pan.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Spread over beans.
Cut green onion tops and all and put over mixture.
Dice the tomato and add over top.
Sprinkle finely shredded Cheddar cheese over all. Serve with your favorite taco chips.

title: chocolate kisses
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 275° for 12 minutes.
Roll in 4x sugar.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Remove fat from meat and cut into strips 1/4 inch wide and 1 1/2 inches long. Brown meat in 3 tablespoons butter; add onion, salt and pepper in pan or heavy skillet. Add bouillon; simmer 1 1/2 hours until tender. Saute mushrooms in rest of butter until lightly browned. Add flour and add to liquid in meat pan, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add mustard and sour cream to pan; mix well and heat to boiling and pour over bed of rice.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, cherry pie filling, almond extract and 2 eggs. Stir by hand until well blended. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until it tests done. Cool.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, egg whites, milk, oil and 1 can coconut. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan about 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Make holes in warm cake with fork.
Pour cream of coconut over cake when cool.
Combine second can of coconut and Cool Whip and frost cake while still in pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: shoe peg corn casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt oleo; mix with crackers.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Frost cake and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water until tender.
Drain well.
Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, egg and onion.
Pour this mixture over broccoli.
Add grated cheese.
Top with stuffing mix and dot with small pieces of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine and dressing. Put 1/2 in bottom of a 9 x 13 dish. Place chicken on top of dressing mixture. Pour soups and chicken broth over chicken. Put the remaining dressing on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: taco potatoes
directions: Brown meat and add bell pepper, onion, seasoning mix and water. Cook until water cooks out and vegies are tender. Serve 1/4 meat mixture over a 3 ounce baked potato. Top with Cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream. Can also top with taco sauce or picante sauce if desired.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Heat butter in heavy skillet and saute onion, garlic and cucumber until onion is tender, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir well.
Gradually stir in broth.
Add salt and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until cucumber is tender.
Cool.
Puree mixture in batches in blender.
Stir or whip in sour cream, dill, lemon rind and mace.
Chill several hours.

title: cucumber congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water; cool.
Puree cucumbers in food processor.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream; mix well, then stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill until slightly congealed, then fold in cucumbers.
