Pour into mold or Pyrex dish, depending on how it is to be served.
Chill in refrigerator until firmly congealed.

title: light lemon chicken
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet.
Add chicken and brown for 3 minutes.
Add broth, peel, tarragon and juice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until meat is no longer pink, 10 to 12 minutes. Remove chicken to serving dish.
Melt 1/2 tablespoon margarine, stir in flour and add juices.
Bring to a boil and stir until it thickens.
Pour over chicken and serve immediately.

title: waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites.
In another large bowl, mix all the ingredients until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook as instructed by waffle iron.

title: chicken wings supreme
directions: Remove tips off
wings.
Place in baking dish.	Combine all ingredients and pour over wings.
Marinate overnight.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: In one or two cup glass measure, combine chocolate pieces and milk.
Heat in microwave oven on High (100%) power for 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir until smooth.
If necessary, return to microwave for 15 seconds.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Add first mushrooms to spaghetti sauce.
Add spaghetti sauce mixture to ground beef.
Add beaten eggs to Ricotta cheese. Spread a layer of sauce mixture over bottom of dish.
Place noodles on top of this and spread Ricotta mixture over noodles. Place a layer of meat sauce over Ricotta.
Add cheeses on top of this.
Start with another layer of noodles, ending with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taku russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons of mixture per cup of hot water.
Recipe from the "Taku Lodge" in Alaska.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients well except crackers. Pour over crackers. Toss lightly until crackers are covered. Store in tightly covered container.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together except margarine, almonds and corn flakes.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine and add corn flakes and almonds.
Sprinkle on top of chicken mixture and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Keep warm. Cook bacon and drain, saving 4 tablespoons drippings.
Add bacon to potatoes.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and sugar.
Then add vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes and serve warm.

title: malt shoppe pie
directions: Combine ice cream and Cool Whip. Blend well. Reserve 8 Whoppers for garnish and crush remaining Whoppers. Add 1 cup crushed candy to ice cream/Cool Whip mixture. Spoon mixture into pie crust. Top with remaining crushed candy.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, green beans, sour cream, soup, cheese, onions, and pepper in casserole dish.
Mix crackers and oleo and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10-12 people.

title: no-fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in 2-quart casserole. Cook in Radarange oven 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Candy thermometer should ready 260°.

If not, cook 1 or 2 minutes longer. While syrup cooks, beat egg whites very stiff in a large bowl. Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites and continue beating at high speed until thick and candy starts to lose its gloss.
Beating may require about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts to beaten mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Yields 7 dozen pieces.
Tint with food coloring for the holiday season.
Be sure to stir candy syrups at least once during cooking, so that the heat is equalized and the candy looks smooth.

title: chuck wagon stew(easy and hearty)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add vegetable soup and beans. Heat for 15 minutes. Serve piping hot with rolls and a tossed salad.

title: tropical garden punch
directions: Chill ingredients. Combine in a punch bowl. Yield: 15 servings.

title: buttermilk chocolate pound cake
directions: In
large bowl beat shortening until creamy.
Gradually add sugar,
beating until mixed well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour.
Add in
thirds to	sugar-egg
mixture alternately with buttermilk (begin and
end with
flour).
On low speed add melted chocolate,	mixing	until well
blended.
Pour
batter evenly into greased 10-inch tube pan or large Bundt pan.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours
or
until	cake tester inserted in center comes out clean at
Cool
for
10 minutes on rack in pan.
Invert cake on
rack
to cool completely. Frost if desired with Dark Chocolate Frosting recipe.

title: chewy gooie cookies
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Put into well-greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.
Score and let cool before slicing and removing from pan.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients as if it were a cake.
Cut out and fry in shortening.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into pan. Bake approximately 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan. Cool before slicing.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Add all ingredients into a blender.
Blend at high speed for 1/2 minute. Remove and add coconut.
Pour mixture into 2 well-buttered and floured glass Pyrex pie plates (9-inches).
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand for 1 hour or longer.

title: shrimp creole - low-fat
directions: Coat a large saucepan with pan spray.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery until tender.
Stir frequently and add a small amount of water, if necessary, to prevent drying.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Heat until sauce just starts to boil. Remove and discard bay leaf.
Reduce heat.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375°.
Pour butter in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: top of the stove cake
directions: In a large Dutch oven, bring water, 2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons butter to a boil.
In a bowl or saucepan, mix remaining butter (melted), remaining sugar, egg, milk, vanilla, flour and cocoa.
Pour this batter into the boiling sauce; turn down low.
Cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, sprinkle top with broken pecans.

title: duftners favorite meal
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat butter and oil in large skillet.
Brown chicken all over.
Season with salt.
Remove chicken.
Drain 2/3 of fat; return to pan and season with pepper and herbs.
Cover with onions.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake 2 to 3 hours.

title: angel food ice cream cake(diabetic)
directions: Cut the cake in half.
Tear half of the cake into small pieces and set aside.
Cut the other half into 12 to 14 thin slices. Arrange in the bottom of a wax paper lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, overlapping the slices as needed.
Spread softened ice cream over cake, pressing down to smooth.
Gently press the small cake pieces into ice cream.
Cover and freeze.
Just before serving, slice strawberries and sweeten with sweetener to taste.
Cut dessert into squares and top with strawberries.
Makes 15 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in casserole dish.
Top with topping and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice; thicken with cornstarch.
Stir in margarine and cinnamon.
Pour thickened apple juice over apples; stir carefully.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour into pie shell; cover with crust.
Brush top with melted margarine or milk; sprinkle with additional cinnamon.
May use unpeeled, grated apples if desired.

title: baked beans
directions: Stir catsup, mustard, brown sugar, onion and molasses in beans. Top with bacon and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli supreme
directions: Combine mayo, flour and seasoning.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick. Add 1 cup cheese and stir until melted. Place broccoli in 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Cover with chicken and sauce. Top with crispy rice squares.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. (Double this for a 13 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish.)

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream can be served on top.

title: sausage bean stew
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, place all ingredients except spinach. Cover and cook over medium heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until barley and lentils are tender. Stir in spinach and heat through.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Prepare biscuit mix according to directions.
Roll out thin. Sprinkle sausage on top and roll into oblong strip.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce to 300° and continue to bake until firm.

title: good and simple-to-make punch
directions: Chill juices.
Pour over sherbet that has been cut up.
Mix sherbet until punch can be poured.

title: shrimp with garlic and tomatoes(scampi con salsa pizzaiola)
directions: Wash
shrimp under cold water.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat oil in
large skillet and saute garlic over medium heat until golden. Remove
garlic
and
discard.
Add
chopped tomatoes, oregano, parsley,
salt and red pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes, add
shrimp and
cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. If
sauce
looks
too dry, you can add a little water.
Heat thoroughly
and
place
in
serving dish.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Great with fresh Italian bread.

title: caldo gallego
directions: Combine the smoked pork, potatoes, collard greens, dry beans, salt pork and water in a large stock pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender. Remove the pork shank from the pot and remove the meat from the bones.
Dice the meat and return to the pot.
Wash the unto to remove salt.
Dice.
Heat the olive oil in a heavy skillet and fry the diced unto until it melts; remove any unto that does not melt and discard.

title: nuts and bolts(great snack.  kids love it!)
directions: Place in a large turkey roaster.
Pour liquid mixture over cereals and thoroughly coat, turning.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours, turning every 15 minutes.
Makes 2 largest Tupperware containers and stores well.
Excellent for Christmas gifts.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk; beat until smooth and creamy.	Prepare dessert topping mix according to package directions; fold into peanut butter mixture.
Turn into prepared crust 5 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in milk; add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir constantly.
Add a dash of cinnamon and with sweet milk to taste. It's good warm or cold.

title: kama's cherry fruitcake(best fruitcake i've ever eaten)
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
Line with foil (allowing a 2-inch overhang) and grease again.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Add fruits and pecans; toss until well coated.
Turn mixture into prepared loaf pans, pressing to pack tightly.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove from pans and take off foil.
Brush loaves with corn syrup while still warm.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: special k-bars
directions: Bring to a boil, sugar and corn syrup; take off stove.
Add peanut butter, then add to Special K.
Spread on a cookie sheet. Melt chips and spread over the other mixture.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers, scoop out seeds.
Cook in boiling water, salted, about 10 minutes.
Drain and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Meanwhile, mix hamburger, eggs, onions, garlic, salt and bread crumbs. Mix together.
Place mixture into pepper. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce on top of pepper and bake another 15 minutes.

title: divine divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to hard ball (260°).
Pour into beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat until it holds its shape and becomes slightly dull.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Do not drop too soon, or it will not hold its shape.
It is delicious!!!

title: idaho potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix last 3 ingredients together and pour over salad.
Leave in refrigerator overnight, then toss.

title: hot chicken dish
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in the margarine.
Add the soups and water to pan; stir.
Heat until hot.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange chicken chunks.
Then pour over the croutons, the mixture of sauteed ingredients and soups.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 16-inch Pyrex baking dish with the crackers.
Beat the pudding with the milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread half of this over the crackers.
Spread remaining pudding mix over the crackers.
Make another layer of crackers. Spread topping over top and let stand overnight.

title: crab and shrimp delite dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Stir in onions and celery along with a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.
With a knife or small spreader, spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour the cocktail sauce over cream cheese and spread.
Spread drained and rinsed shrimp and crab over top.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Serve with Breton crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: elaine's cornbread and corn medley
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
After 30 minutes put cheese on top and bake for remaining 10 minutes.
Great for a potluck when you can't think of anything to bring.
Can be served hot or cold.
Best hot, though.
You can spray Pam in pan if you want.
Makes easier to get out of the pan.

title: feather dumplings
directions: Add butter to beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Drop by teaspoons into boiling broth and cook covered 18 minutes.

title: green tomato goulash
directions: Fry all ingredients in bacon grease or Crisco until it's done. You can even can this, but don't use bacon grease or Crisco; use water.

title: dove or quail in wine sauce
directions: Salt and pepper birds.
Dust with flour and brown in oil. Place onions and celery in bottom of large Dutch oven.
Put bay leaves inside each bird and dot with butter.
Pour wine and water over birds.
Cover and bake at 375° about 2 hours or until birds are fully cooked.
Baste often.
Serve with long grain or wild rice.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Bring stew to boil, using 2 cups water.
Simmer for 4 hours. Mix 1 cup meat broth with remaining ingredients; boil 20 minutes. Pour over cooked meat that has been shredded.
Simmer for 1 hour; let stand 2 hours to bring out the flavor.
(Add water as needed in the 4 hour cooking time.)
Serve on buns.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water and cook until thick; add jello.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with lots of strawberries. This is enough for 1 pie; to double add whole package of jello.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix together.
Beat 12 minutes with mixer.

title: ann's molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add molasses and soda, beat until foamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add water and all dry ingredients, beat until smooth.
Allow to cool several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out and bake in 400° oven 12 - 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans and apples; blend. Fold in pecans and apples.
Bake in layers at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: big pretzels
directions: Mix together the oil, garlic powder, dill weed and dressing; mix.
Break pretzels.
Put on cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After 10 minutes, turn.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: sour cream bran muffins
directions: Cream oleo; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, sour cream and molasses.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add bran, stirring just until moist.
Spoon into baking cups or greased muffin tins.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Very good!

title: mushroom rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curried rice-a-roni
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Put in a large bowl and add mayonnaise, olives, artichokes and curry powder.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fresh fruit delight
directions: Peel and slice peaches and bananas; sprinkle with Fruit-Fresh to keep from turning brown.
Drain pineapple chunks.
Slice strawberries; reserve a few for garnish.
Cut cantaloupe and honeydew.
Mix all fruit together.
Mix pudding and 3/4 of Cool Whip together.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Mix together 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls in the cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy pizza buns(snack)
directions: On ungreased cookie sheet, place halved buns (as many as desired).
Butter buns.
Put one slice of cheese on each.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons sauce on each.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute liver and diced
onions
in
1/4 cup butter. Then put all ingredients in a
food	processor and blend well.
Add salt to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: low-fat pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and small amount of flour.
Stir until smooth.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour on counter. Gradually stir in remaining flour.
Remove dough from bowl and knead in last of flour.
Knead until smooth.
Divide dough in half, roll into circles and put on 2 pizza pans.
Pierce with fork.
Let rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake crust 15 minutes.
Then top with your choice of green peppers, low-fat ham, ground turkey breast, low-fat pizza sauce, no-fat Mozzarella cheese and sliced tomatoes.
Bake 10 minutes.
After prebaking crust, you can cover with foil and freeze for later.
Thaw while the oven preheats and then add your toppings.
Bake at 400°.
Contains 5
grams of fat in the whole pizza.

title: mini cheese balls
directions: Freeze the dried apricots and apples for 1 to 2 hours and you will be able to chop them much more easily.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Roll into small balls. Place on baking sheet and press down with tumbler dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potatoes and 1 cup warm water; then add 1 package yeast.
Put in jar with lid on. Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.
Take out and feed the following:
3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potatoes and 1 cup warm water. Mix well; add to starter, let stand out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours.
Take out 1 cup to make bread and return mixture to refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days and feed again.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt bars in syrup over boiling water.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda with milk and add alternately with flour.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: real banana pudding
directions: Combine flour and sugar together, then add egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Stir slowly over low heat, preferably in double boiler until it strikes a boil.
Let cook about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add bananas and wafers.
Let cool.

title: coffee chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts. Brown in butter in hot skillet.
Then place in casserole dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and simmer in same skillet until well blended.
Pour over chicken. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream butter and eggs first, then add cake mix.
Spread out in cake pan.
Put a layer of chopped nuts over mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Put 1/3 of bread cubes in bottom of pan, then chicken mixture, then rest of cubes.
Pour a mixture of 2 beaten eggs and 1 1/2 cups of milk over chicken and bread. Refrigerate 4 hours or more.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.

Place 2/3 of the batter in pan, spreading evenly. Add 1 can cherry, apricot or blueberry pie filling, spreading over the batter. Drop remaining batter by tablespoonfuls onto pie filling. Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze while warm (1 cup powdered sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons milk).

title: creamed chicken with vegetables
directions: In skillet, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add chicken.
Cook until tender.
Stir in vegetables and potatoes.
Heat through.

title: 16-bean soup
directions: Quick Soak Method:
Sort and rinse beans into large pot. Cover beans with 3 cups hot water.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
If you wish, you can microwave beans in a covered 2 1/2 to 3-quart pan for 10 minutes.

title: no-fat banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and egg whites in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add the apple and put into a greased (Pam sprayed) loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pan to rack; let cool.

title: quick fat free dessert
directions: Put 1/10 of cake (1 slice) on dessert plate.
Place fruit on top.
Put 2 tablespoons Cool Whip on top.
Drizzle 1 teaspoon chocolate syrup over top.
Fat:
0 grams.
Calories:
150 to 200 (depending on fruit.)

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast and water in large bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients except flour.
Stir.
Add 5 cups flour and stir.
Add rest of flour and stir real good.
Seal, burp and let stand until seal pops off.
Grease and flour hands and divide into 3 loaves. Cover with a towel.
Let stand 40 minutes.
Time varies depending on how many loaves you are making.
You can make bread, doughnuts, dinner rolls, sweet rolls, cinnamon rolls or tea rings.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven until golden brown.

title: huckleberry cheesecake
directions: Mix well crushed graham crackers, sugar and butter.
Pack lightly in 9 X 13 pan.

title: light buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Bake on hot griddle.
Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: In double boiler, sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften; heat over hot water until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, extract and berries.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Then fold in whipped cream; refrigerate until stiff enough to spread.
Use to fill and frost sponge layers.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake in greased pans for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh breakfast patties
directions: On medium heat in nonstick skillet, cook onion and apple in oil for 5 minutes, stirring until soft.
Let stand until cool.
In bowl, combine turkey, thyme, fennel, allspice, pepper and nutmeg. Add cooled onion and apple.
Shape into patties.
Heat nonstick skillet on medium heat.
Cook about 3 1/2 minutes per side until browned and done.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Bake half the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan; let cool.
Beat pudding, cream cheese and milk; spread on top of cake.
Spread on crushed pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: fishy shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: fruit 'n yogurt dazzler
directions: In small saucepan
combine
egg yolks, honey, water and cornstarch; mix well.
Cook
and
stir
over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat, cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Spoon mixture
into a small bowl.	Cover with plastic wrap;
chill mixture
without
stirring for several hours.	At serving time, fold	egg
yolk
mix into yogurt, blending well. In a large
glass
bowl
or
individual parfait glasses, layer fruit and yogurt mixture, ending with yogurt on top.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Garnish
with
whole fruit, if desired. Makes about 10 servings.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Cook onion in butter in Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add carrots and 1 cup broth.
Bring to a boil; cover reduce heat and simmer until carrots are tender.
Carefully spoon into blender; process until smooth.
Return to Dutch oven; add remaining broth, half and half, pepper and salt.
Cook over low until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly.
With a wire whisk, stir in yogurt, at room temperature, and dill weed.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: banana bread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together egg whites, bananas, sugar and oil.
Stir flour mixture into banana mixture just until moistened.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray coating.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool bread in the pan for 10 minute.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly on a wire rack.

title: desperation dinner
directions: In a large pot, brown the sliced sausage and onions.
Open all the cans and add to the pot; don't drain.
Cover and cook on medium to low as long as you want.
It is ready in about 20 minutes, but can be started in
the morning and cooked all day in a low crock-pot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until slightly tender; drain.
Set aside.
Brown ground meat and onion in small skillet.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Oil a 1-quart casserole dish and spoon in 1/3 of meat mixture.
Add cooked macaroni, then remainder of meat mixture.
Spread cheese soup over all.
(May be frozen, unbaked.) Cover tightly and bake at 400° until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Simmer onion and butter.
Mix ingredients with sauce.
Cook slowly 1 1/2 hours.

title: egg nog
directions: Put in blender and blend until mixed well.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in stick of margarine.
Add cooked rice.
Combine with remaining ingredients and turn into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana-walnut scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions but do not let stand.
Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange 3 chicken pieces on each side of stuffing, overlapping if necessary.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Fill cooled pie shell with sliced strawberries.
Combine Jello, 7 up, and cornstarch in saucepan.
Heat until thickened. Let cool and pour over berries.
Top with De zerta Whip Topping.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Mix broccoli, cornbread mix, eggs and cottage cheese.
Mix with butter and onion.
Stir in baking powder.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut in squares and serve while hot.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: Put macaroni, chicken and cheese in pan; pour broth over it. Mix melted oleo with bread crumbs and put on top.
Brown in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in bananas and nuts, then flour, baking soda and salt. Spread in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: freeze punch
directions: Bring to a
boil sugar and water.
Remove from heat and add both packages
of jello.
Then stir in pineapple juice and add 2 cans
of
water.
Freeze.
Remove
from
freezer 4 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: clusters
directions: Melt chips and pour over peanuts and noodles.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: In bowl, combine beans, corn, sour cream, cheese and onion. Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, crumbs and almonds, sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Saute beef until brown; drain. Drain and rinse beans. Chop tomatoes and onion; tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients. Toss well. Serve at once. Serves 10 to 12.

title: griddlecakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine the egg, milk, and fat.
Add gradually to the dry ingredients; stir only until batter is smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a hot greased griddle.
Cook slowly until the surface is covered with bubbles, turn, and cook until the bottom is well browned.
Yields:
about 18 medium-sized griddlecakes.

title: individual cheese cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.

title: layered green salad
directions: Use a large glass salad bowl and layer from the bottom up the ingredients.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Do not mix!
Each person is supposed to serve by reaching through all layers to get a little of each.

title: chocolate pecan butterballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine margarine, confectioners' sugar, cocoa, vanilla, and flour.

Beat until well mixed. This will be a thick mixture. Work the pecans into the cookie dough. Roll the dough into balls about 1 inch in diameter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Coat with confectioners' sugar as cookies are removed from baking sheet. Place on rack to cool. Coat with confectioners' sugar again after the cookies have cooled. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons grated lemon rind, lemon juice, egg yolks and milk.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Place dish into pan of water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool.
Can then be refrigerated after it is cool.

title: jalapeno hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add onion and all peppers.
Use enough buttermilk to make to consistency of cornbread.
Test batter by putting a small amount in hot grease or oil.
If it does not rise well, add a little more baking powder.
If the hush puppies are too greasy or break apart, add a little more flour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries, oranges and pecans.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Add all ingredients together, stir.
Pour into Pyrex dish and refrigerate until jelled.

title: chicken crunch ole
directions: Mix soup, water and hot pepper sauce.
Dust chicken with flour; dip in 1/2 cup soup mixture.
Roll in chips.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Heat remaining sauce; serve with chicken. Makes 4 servings.

title: oven baked steak
directions: Don't salt meat.
Put meat in a deep baking dish and cover with a mixture of canned soups.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top. Wrap the baking dish completely in foil.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and set aside for 2 hours. Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the cabbage mixture and mix well.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until done, drain.
Melt 1 stick of butter and add a little flour as though making gravy.
Cook just until flour and butter is well blended.
Stir in enough milk to make a thin sauce.
Bring to a boil and add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Use a baking dish and layer 1/2 of cabbage then 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers.
Melt stick of butter and stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake until crackers are brown.

title: broccoli soup 1
directions: Cook frozen broccoli in water until tender.
Add soups.
Mix together and warm until desired temperature.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in large, heavy saucepan.
Slowly bring to a boil and boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter, chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Mix until chips and marshmallows are melted.
Add vanilla and nuts; blend.
Spread in large ungreased pan and let cool.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: caramelized pineapple(servings:  8)
directions: Cut pineapple in half.
With a sharp grapefruit knife, cut pulp from shell without damaging the shell.
Cut pineapple pulp into 1-inch cubes.
In a skillet over medium heat, toss cubes with brown sugar until caramelized.
Serve in hollowed out pineapple shell.

title: brunswick stew(serve with barbecue or seafood)
directions: Place meat in large, heavy pot.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onions and cover with water.
Cook until meat falls from bones (several hours).
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Tear meat into shreds and return to stock.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop up cranberries; place in colander and place in bowl. Pour sugar over cranberries; let drain overnight.
(Discard juice in bowl.)

title: scalloped corn
directions: Arrange in two layers in a greased baking dish the corn mixed with the eggs, salt and onion.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Pour over with milk.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for about 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: party punch
directions: Make lemonade according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy chocolate delight pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of the chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large microwavable bowl at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, milk in a 2 1/2 qt. saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat; stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts, and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 9x13 inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: crab melt-a-ways
directions: Split and cut muffins in quarters.
Mix ingredients and add 1/2 pound crabmeat.
Spread on muffin quarters and freeze single on cookie sheet for at least 1/2 hour.
Put in freezer bags and freeze until ready to use.
Broil until bubbly and golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 48.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cover onions and cook in butter in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, until tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add water, pepper, thyme, bay leaf and broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Set oven control to broil.
Place 1 slice toasted bread in each of 4 ovenproof bowls. Pour in onions and broth; top with Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place bowls on cookie sheet.
Broil with tops of bowls about 5 inches from heat, just until the cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and let stand for
minutes.
Make balls and fry in deep fat.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In baking dish, place green beans. Top with soup and milk. Top with the French fried onions. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mert's summer fish
directions: The trick to this recipe is speed.
Pour powdered Italian dressing and flour into a bag. Shake well. Add fish and shake well.
Place fish in hot corn oil.
Fry approximately 5 minutes on medium-high heat or until golden brown.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients to rice.
Toss gently.
Bake in buttered casserole in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
This can be prepare a day ahead and refrigerated and baked before serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin tin.
Mix cereal and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Beat in oil and egg.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until moist.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: upside-down pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Freezes well.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat 10 minutes: egg, sugar, oil, juice and vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Coat apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Fold into batter.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornstarch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla. Mix in flour and cornstarch.
Form into 1 inch balls, place on baking sheet and flatten slightly.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and place in a 13 x 9 Pyrex pan. Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour.

title: alabama chicken
directions: Crumble 2 packages of crackers into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with 1/4 cup margarine.
Remove chicken from the bones and cut into bite size pieces, spread over crackers.
Spread mushrooms and water chestnuts over the chicken.
Mix together the soups and sour cream, spread over top.
Crumble remaining crackers and put on top of creamed soup mix.
Dot with remaining margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until good and hot.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and form crust in the bottom of 2-quart baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Blend together eggs, 4x sugar, melted margarine and vanilla.
Spread over cooled crust.
Slice bananas overfilling, spread crushed pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Work first four ingredients together.
Roll into small balls. Put the last two ingredients in a double boiler and melt.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and cool on wax paper.
Keep chocolate mixture on a low fire during the dipping.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat eggs, then add rest of mixture together.
Mix well, spoon out and bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine together.
Put a layer of graham cracker crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip, cold milk and whip.
Add sugar and cream cheese in the Dream Whip.
Put layer of cream cheese mix on crust, put pie filling on cream cheese and add rest of the cream cheese, and sprinkle the rest of the graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: butterscotch rolls(serves 8)
directions: Place frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Mix butterscotch pudding and brown sugar; sprinkle over frozen rolls.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the last mixture.
Place chopped pecans on top.
Pour melted butter over pecans.
Let set overnight or at least 8 hours, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lynne's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease 2 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans.
Mix together:
sugar, shortening, eggs and water.
In another bowl, mix together sifted flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add to first mixture.
Mash ripe bananas and add into mixture. Add chopped walnuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add onions and mix.
Add egg and milk. Stir.
Drop from teaspoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: date nut crackers
directions: Combine dates, milk and pecans in saucepan.
Cook slowly over medium to high heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture reaches the consistency of peanut butter.
Spread mixture on Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 450° oven for 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with frosting.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice and pecan rice (separately) according to package directions; set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan; saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; cook over low heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms, broth and half and half.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in rices, chicken, pimiento, parsley and seasoning.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole; top with almonds and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Yield:
About 8 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Wash and boil beets until tender.
Peel beets while warm or you may use canned beets. Cut into slices.
Mix cornstarch, salt, sugar and pepper in a 2-quart saucepan.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add beets.
Heat and serve.
Makes 4 servings.
With fresh beets this recipe cans well.
Be careful to measure and increase ingredients accordingly.

title: myrtle's shrimp gumbo
directions: Combine oil, onions, celery, garlic, paprika and okra in heavy pot.
Cook slowly until limp.
Add next gumbo file to heat a minute or two to impart flavor and prevent "ropiness".
Add to pot, cover and let simmer 15 minutes or longer.
Can tomatoes, chicken stock (may use cubes), salt and red and black pepper.
Add shrimp to cook no longer than 10 minutes.

title: chicken feed (dog food)
directions: Melt chips, butter and peanut butter together.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, then coat Chex.
Put powdered sugar in grocery sack; shake and add coated Chex.
Shake again.
Store in large plastic bag.
Makes 9 cups.
Can be served in a clean dog dish.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in large microwavable bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring halfway through heating time.
(The chocolate will retain some of its original shape.)
Remove from the oven.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Refrigerate about 10 minutes to cool.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon onto crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature or until pie can be easily cut.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: date cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add dates, sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook about ten minutes, stirring constantly, until bubbly. Remove from heat; add cereal, nuts and vanilla.
With tablespoon, form into ball and roll in flaked coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat in a medium saucepan. Add remaining ingredients in the order listed, stirring after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
For 1 serving, combine 1/3 cup cocoa mixture and 3/4 cup boiling water. Makes 45 (8 ounce) servings.

title: old fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
Chill, if necessary.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Flatten with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes (light brown). Remove warm.
Cool on rack.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Line the bottoms and sides of a 8 inch cake pan or 1 1/2 quart baking dish with wafers.
Combine pudding mix, milk and butter in a sauce pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a greased sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on English muffins.
Freeze for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into quarters.
Wait 15 minutes; defrost.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef minestrone
directions: Cook meat in Dutch oven; cook onion until tender. Add water and other ingredients except Parmesan. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Discard bay leaf. Sprinkle Parmesan over each serving. Serves 10.

title: mom's apricot crisp
directions: Pour apricots (juice and all) in an oblong Pyrex dish. Sweeten to taste.
Sprinkle with tapioca. Dot with butter and let set 30 minutes.

title: carrot pudding *
directions: Cook and mash carrots; add all the other ingredients.
Put in greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Can be doubled.

title: lasagna
directions: Set aside
12 thin slices Mozzarella cheese and half of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix beef and egg; form into cocktail size balls. Brown in skillet. Add meatballs to sauce and heat thoroughly. Cook in crock-pot. The longer in the sauce the better they taste. Serve with toothpicks or in a bed of rice.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and then put a layer of dough and nut mixture in a tube pan.
Place the remaining half of the batter in pan and sprinkle with the remaining half of cinnamon and nut mixture.
Bake in tube pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: monte carlo sandwiches
directions: On each of 4 bread slices, place 1 slice each of ham, turkey and cheese.
Cover with remaining slices of bread.
In a shallow bowl, beat eggs, milk and salt and mix well.
Dip each sandwich carefully into egg mixture, turning to dip each side.
Fry in oiled pan or grill on medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes per side or until golden brown and meat is hot and cheese is melted.

title: garlic-butter vegetables
directions: On a large microwave-safe platter, arrange broccoli and cauliflower around outer edge.
Sprinkle with water.
Cover with microwave-safe clear plastic wrap; vent by leaving a small area unsealed at the edge.
Micro-cook on 100% power (High) for 2 minutes.
Place zucchini, mushrooms and peppers in center.
Cook, covered, on High for 4 to 5 minutes more, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Carefully drain off liquid.
Drizzle with Garlic Butter.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and mold.
Pour cocktail sauce over before serving.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut vegetables and chicken in bite sizes.
In a large frypan, heat oil and cook chicken and onions.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and simmer in juices.
Steam carrots and broccoli in microwave until done, about 3 1/2 minutes.
Vegetables should be slightly crisp. Add to chicken and add gourmet sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Cook rice as instructed.
Serve chicken over rice.

title: salmon and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the potatoes, onion, celery, chicken broth, garlic, salt and marjoram.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in cream and milk with butter (I substitute milk for cream).
Combine flour and corn and stir in soup.
Heat, but do not boil, just until thickened.
Gently stir in salmon and heat through.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: easy and thick barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pepper.
Heat.
When warm, stir in pepper.
You can vary this according to how hot you like sauce.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and mix with all the other ingredients.
Pour in baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: carrot-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake until done.

title: vegetarian-cream cheese spread
directions: In medium bowl, with electric mixer on high speed, beat cream cheese, garlic and pepper until well blended.
Stir in green onions, radishes and olives.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight to allow time for flavors to blend.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: macaroni paprikash
directions: Cook elbow according to directions; drain and return to pot. Saute onion in butter in large skillet and push aside.
Shape ground beef into a large patty in the same pan.
Brown 5 minutes on both sides and then break up into chunks.
Blend in flour, paprika, salt, bouillon cube, milk, mushrooms, liquid from mushrooms and water.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils for 1 minute.
Blend about 1/2 cup of the hot mixture into the sour cream, then stir back into pan.
Stir into cooked macaroni; add parsley.
Put into greased casserole, sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Put Jell-O in bowl.
Add pineapple, whip cream and marshmallows.
Stir well.
Mix all ingredients together well.

title: snappy barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine catsup, water, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, celery seed and bottled hot pepper sauce.
Bring the catsup mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well and add chicken strips. Marinate at least 1 hour.
Heat nonstick skillet and cook chicken until no longer pink.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add onion and bell pepper strips to pan.
Cook covered until tender.
Squeeze lime juice into pan.
Serve on hot corn or flour shells.

title: pickledilly chowder
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions and salt; let stand overnight.
Drain and add vinegar and water and cook 20 minutes.
Drain and add 1 quart vinegar, sugar, peppers, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and mustard seed.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Can in pint jars or smaller.
Makes about 5 to 6 pints.

title: hot light potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: kapusta
directions: Saut onion in oleo.
Mix cabbage, sauerkraut, bay leaf and sauted onions.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add 1-inch of water. Continue baking until cabbage is done (approximately 1/2 hour).

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soups and rice; set aside.
Grease casserole.
Place chicken in it. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Do not peek.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sweet sour beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Into the skillet with bacon drippings, place the vinegar and sugar.
Add drained beans.
Simmer 25 minutes, turning occasionally.
When ready to serve, top with bacon.
These reheat well.
Serves 4.

title: tomato relish
directions: Place tomatoes and liquid into small bowl; cut tomatoes into very small pieces.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a pint jar; cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator several hours before using.
Serve with hot or cold meats, beans or dried peas.

title: oatmeal apple butter bars
directions: Cut margarine into flour and sugar until crumbly.
Stir in oatmeal.
Press 1/2 of mixture firmly into greased 8-inch pan. Spread apple butter within 1/2 inch of edge.
Sprinkle remaining oatmeal mixture over apple butter.
Press carefully but firmly. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough out on a pizza sheet and bake.
Mix Ranch dressing, cream cheese and mayonnaise. Spread on top of crust when cooled. Put on vegetables and sprinkle on the cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in butter; cook spaghetti noodles (drain).
Debone chicken.
Mix chicken, onions and bell pepper with Worcestershire sauce, then Velveeta cheese and tomatoes in large pot.
Keep heat on medium until cheese melts.

title: marshmallows
directions: Put gelatine and cold water in large crockery bowl; let stand. Cook sugar, hot water and cream of tartar until it threads well. When it threads, hard ball stage, add to gelatine and beat constantly for about 15 minutes on medium speed with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and coloring; mix.
Line pan with buttered waxed paper and sprinkle heavy with powdered sugar.
Pour the marshmallow mixture into it and sprinkle top with more powdered sugar.
It may be cut with a knife or scissors when cool.
Cut off in strips and then cut the strips into pieces.
Dip each piece in powdered sugar and the pieces won't stick together.
Note:
I use a 9 X 13 pan.

title: bubble loaf or monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in plastic bag. Shake bits thoroughly until covered well.
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan.
Pour melted margarine, sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts over.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put on plate immediately.

title: pig roasted in pit
directions: You will also need a shovel, wood, rocks, a potato bag, gunny sacks, kerosene, matches and chicken wire.

title: chicken creole
directions: Broil fryer 10 minutes on each side, after sprinkling salt and paprika on it.
In electric skillet, combine tomatoes and all other ingredients together.
Bring to a boil; add chicken pieces. Cover and simmer 40 minutes over low heat.
Serve with rice or noodles and a salad.

title: dried lima beans and bacon
directions: Cover beans with water; bring to a boil and simmer over a medium fire
for
hour.
Add
crisp crumbled bacon, salt, pepper and onion.
Cover
and cook until beans are tender, not mushy.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: butter mints
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add oil of peppermint.
Add milk to make a dough-like consistency.
Add color if desired.
Mold in rubber candy molds.
Allow to dry at least 24 hours before packing in tins.

title: chocolate orange tea drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, cream cheese, sugar, egg, orange rind and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together and stir in.
Stir in chocolate pieces, mixing thoroughly.
Drop teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake about 15 minutes, until cookies are delicately browned at edges.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip blondies
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch dish with nonstick spray (or grease with butter).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt. In separate bowl, mix egg, vanilla, margarine, vegetable oil, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add flour mixture to this bowl; stir thoroughly.
Finally, stir in chocolate chips.
Turn into greased dish, spreading cookie dough evenly with a spatula.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes, until golden.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and 1 stick margarine.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick of margarine.
Add eggs.
To this mixture add alternately the flour with soda and buttermilk.
Add melted candy and margarine mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: non-greasy cracklin cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add buttermilk to make thinner batter.
Pour into 9-inch greased skillet.
Bake at 450° until brown on top.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: In top of double boiler combine sugar, cold water, egg whites, corn syrup and a dash of salt.
Beat 30 seconds on low speed of mixer.
Place over boiling water (upper pan should not touch water).
Cook about 7 minutes while beating constantly on high speed of mixer or until frosting forms stiff peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes or until of spreading consistency.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Mix noodles and sour cream.
Add 1/2 cup cheese. Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top lightly with remaining cheese.
Bake about an hour at 225°.

title: sunday macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Put back into sauce pan. Stir in margarine, milk, and cheese together. Add salt, pepper, sugar & tomatoes. Pour into 2 qt. casserole dish. Add more shredded cheese over top if desired. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: dot hinshaw's peach ice cream
directions: Blend peaches, eggs and sugar.
Whip the 3 milks together. Freeze in freezer.
You can leave the eggs out of the recipe if desired.
May substitute any fresh fruit.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar in a bowl. Cut in butter with a fork until crumbly.
Add buttermilk and mix quickly to make a soft dough.
Place on a lightly floured surface. Knead a few times.
Roll into a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
With a floured knife, cut across dough 2 times in one directions and 3 times in the opposite direction, making 12 equal portions.
Do not separate!
Bake at 400° until golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Brush with melted butter and serve hot.

title: autumn apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in eggs.
Sift next 4 ingredients; add alternately with coarsely grated, peeled apples to egg mixture.
Stir in lemon rind and nuts. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: sawdust cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in oatmeal, wheat germ and corn flakes.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder; add to mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put in your bread (buttered on both sides).
Then in large mixing bowl, add your eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle grated cheese. Then pour mixture over your ham or sausage.

title: high protein bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and carob chips over medium heat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into a greased 5 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Line pie pan with crust.
Put pecans in layer.
Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pink cloud dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Good, unexpected dinner guest dessert.
Fast and easy!

title: peach bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Combine the next 5 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with peaches, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in orange juice and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Cook milk, chocolate, marshmallows and salt in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt and mixture thickens.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan or two 1-quart ice trays with wafers.
Spoon half of ice cream and chocolate over.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate 5 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop drained artichokes fine.
Add cheese and mayonnaise until smooth, but not well blended.
Don't stir too much or mayonnaise breaks down.
Add garlic to taste.
Cook at 300° for approximately 30 minutes or until top browns slightly.
Serve warm with sturdy corn chips.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and cauliflower.
Toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6.

title: kart-wheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, butter, powdered sugar, baking powder and milk until dough forms.
Divide dough into 6 parts.
Shape each part into a ball and place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Make an indentation in the center of each ball (about 1 3/4-inches round and 3/4-inch deep).
Fill indentation with about 2 tablespoons pie filling.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 Kart-Wheels.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls into round pizza pan, overlapping edges and press down to seal, this forming the crust.
Cook sausage scrambled and drain.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with hash browns. Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat well and pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl. Then roll into small balls.
Brown meatballs in deep skillet until done. Then make a brown gravy and cook together with meatballs.
Serve over rice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chili sauce and mustard.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Layer hamburger and vegetables.
Pour soup and water over all. Bake an hour or until vegetables are done.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all except broccoli.
Grease pan and add all together. Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Frost with Creamy Chocolate Frosting and cut into 24 squares.

title: pork chops with glazed apples
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Add pork chops; sprinkle with sage. Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink in center.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet.
Keep warm.
Add apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over chops.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine, mixing until well blended. Add flour; mix well.
Chill.
Divide dough into quarters, divide each quarter into 12 balls.
Press each ball into bottom and sides of miniature muffin pans.
Combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla. Stir in pecans.
Spoon into pastry shells filling each cup.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: herbed pasta alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat. Add onions and garlic; saute 2 minutes. Add flour and stir well.
Gradually add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheeses and herbs. Serve over macaroni. Garnish with extra onions, if desired.
Contains 244 calories and 4.3 grams fat per serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Chill, then serve on lettuce.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Place flour and salt in large bowl.
Cream sugar and margarine in separate bowl, then add boiling water.
Melt yeast in warm water.
Add cold water to bowl with sugar and margarine, then quickly add yeast mixture and eggs and beat until smooth.
Pour that mixture into flour mixture and mix well with wooden spoon. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to one week.
To make cloverleaf dinner rolls, pinch off three walnut sized pieces of dough and place in cupcake tin side by side.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° or until golden.
Excellent, quick and easy!

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in airtight container.

title: fruit juice medley
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: marinated mozzarella
directions: Place cheese in a single layer in a 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan. In a small bowl, whisk next 6 ingredients.
Pour oil mixture over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend, turning slices occasionally.
Arrange on a serving plate; garnish with fresh basil.
Serve with bagel chips or crackers.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Heat margarine and water in saucepan until boiling.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Beat in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour thin batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, butter and salt.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and vinegar.
Pour over hot cooked green beans.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in apples and coconut.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock lemon meringue cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan. Cool and cut into three layers. Stir pudding and pie filling until smooth.
Spread 1/3 of filling between each layer and on top of cake.
Frost the layers and sides with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ho - ho cake
directions: Mix cake according to the package and put in greased and floured jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) and bake; cool.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except Swiss cheese.
Spread in an 11 x
x
1	3/4-inch
baking
dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle
Swiss cheese on top.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes
or
until	knife
inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: taco chili bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat chili, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Mix Bisquick and milk until dough forms; beat 30 seconds. Spread half the dough in ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Top with chili; sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese.
Drop remaining dough by 6 spoonfuls onto top; sprinkle with paprika. Bake until light brown, about 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
shortening
and
sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs,
one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Baked in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour 25 minutes to 325°.

title: chocolate cherry cordial drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cookie mix, egg and water in large bowl. Stir until blended. Stir in cherries and coconut. Shape dough into 36 balls. Roll in pecans. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are lightly brown. Cool 1 minute, then remove to cooling rack.

title: spaghetti bolognaise
directions: Brown the ground beef, drain away fat and set to one side.

In a large pan heat the oil and add the onion and garlic, cook until soft but not brown. Add the beef to the pan and stir to heat through. Chop the tomatoes well, add with the puree. Add the Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and gravy mix Bring to a boil then reduce and simmer for about 1 hour. If necessary thicken with corn starch which has been added to a little water. Boil the spaghetti for about 7 minutes, do not over cook. Drain and rinse with boiling water. Serve sauce over the spaghetti, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine next seven ingredients, add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in vanilla, raisins and pecans. Spoon into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for
1 hour or until wooden pick tests clean. Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: mango sherbet
directions: Combine puree, 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and 1/2 cup water. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour into a container and freeze to a mushy consistency.

title: hamburger barbecue filling
directions: Get out Mother's heaviest frying pan and put all ingredients, except rolls, in it.
Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Fill the rolls with mixture.
Serve hot.

title: drain maintenance
directions: Mix in quart jar.
Shake well.
Pour 1/4 cup of th dry mix in drain followed immediately with 1 cup boiling water.
When the bubbling in the drain pipe stops, flush thoroughly with cold water.

title: mountain cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in a separate bowl.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add cornmeal, milk and flour.
Add melted butter, baking powder and salt.
Pour into a greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° until golden brown and done.
Cut into large slices.
Serves 6.

title: chicken tremendous
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread contents of onion soup mix.
Add layer of uncooked rice.
Mix can of soup with water. Pour 1/2 over rice and soup mix.
Place chicken pieces on top. Pour remaining water and soup mixture over chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 375°
for 1 hour, uncovered. Add extra water if needed.

title: beef and rice skillet
directions: Brown in oleo, bacon fat or oil steak and onion.
Add rice and remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour until meat and rice are tender.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream and eggs with mixer until blended. Add cherry pie filling and mix by hand until blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Generously grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt cake pan; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the flours, granulated sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add oil, vanilla and eggs; beat until well mixed.
Stir in chopped apples and nuts.
Spoon batter evenly into prepared pan.

title: french apricot cream cheese bars
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and egg with fork until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Spread apricot jam over crust.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over jam.
Sprinkle reserved topping over cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl,
stir
together the flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in
the
beaten
eggs
until	the mixture is moistened.	Fold in
zucchini.
Pour
oil
in skillet 1/8-inch and heat.
Drop
slightly rounded tablespoonfuls of the batter into oil. Cook, turning once
for
about 1 minute on each side or until golden brown.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top each chicken piece with lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: gooey pecan bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter.
Press into bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and remaining 1/2 cup butter; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in pecans; pour over cake mix layer.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until set, covering loosely with aluminum foil after 45 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello powder into cottage cheese.
Fold in mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple.

title: seasoned salt
directions: *BLKLIN plate; heat for 30 to 45 seconds.
Let stand for 1 minute to recrisp.
Recrisp dry cereal the same way.

title: bee's bingo cherry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the gelatin and hot water.
Add the pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch pan; chill until set.
Soften the cream cheese; mix well with the sugar.
Blend in the sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over the gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Serves 6.

title: soap crayons
directions: Grease plastic ice cube tray or popsicle molds with Pam or shortening.
Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into trays or molds.
Allow time to harden.
Pop out.

title: blueberry pudding pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Spread over crust.
Cook blueberries, sugar and flour until thickened.
Cool and spread over pudding.
Cover with whipping cream and vanilla. Chill and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix altogether, except 1/2 cup nuts, and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining nuts.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in water to cover until tender; drain.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Mix rice and broccoli.
Add jar of Cheez Whiz.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to rice mixture.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add mushroom soup.
Pour into buttered large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate bars
directions: Combine crumbs and sugar in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate and evaporated milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Blend well. Add vanilla and set aside 1/2 cup chocolate mixture.
Stir in crumbs mixture and spread into a well-buttered 9-inch square pan. Spread rest of chocolate over top.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: teenager's delight
directions: Spread	cooked	and
drained ground beef over bottom of casserole dish.
Mix
soups and milk and pour over beef layer. Cover with the Tater Tots. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle some grated Cheddar cheese over top for the last 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel apples and cut into chunks.
Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon in a bowl; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl with electric mixer.
In greased cake pan, layer the batter, apples, batter, apples, etc.
Always start and end with batter.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Top with sifted powdered sugar when cool.

title: southern pecan pie(9-inch pie)
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla, and pecan pieces.
Pour filling into prepared pie shell.
Arrange the pecan halves around the inside edge.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 40 minutes longer or until the center is firm.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix dry jello with sour cream and mix with Cool Whip, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Chill.
Can be used for dessert or for a salad.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Pare and slice the potatoes.
Put in a casserole dish.
Lightly salt and pepper the potatoes.
In a mixing bowl, mix Lipton onion soup mix with milk.
Fry pork chops in 1/4 cup oil on both sides until browned.
Drain chops on paper towel and arrange them on top of potatoes.
Pour soup mixture on top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: old fashioned tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil, add baking soda, garlic salt, pepper and salt. Reduce heat: add the milk and butter. Heat through, but do not boil. Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Pour this over bacon stuff.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cut and serve.
(You can use ham instead of bacon.) Serves 6.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer dip:
bottom layer, refried beans, next layer sour cream, then salsa, then guacamole, then jalapenos, then cheese and last black olives.
Chill and eat!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into a ball. Roll in paprika and refrigerate.

title: lemon torte
directions: Cream oleo; add flour and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown (very light); cool.

title: beef teriyaki and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and seasonings.
Add beef; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.
Stir-fry beef in hot oil in skillet until browned.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Mix broth and cornstarch; add to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Prepare 4 servings of Minute rice as directed on package. Serve beef mixture over rice.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper.
Arrange layers of potatoes, onions and soup mix in 2-quart casserole.
Dot top with margarine and sprinkle of paprika.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour in 375° oven.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes or until done.
Enjoy.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar & salt.
Add egg and cream.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan - bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: papa's southern style sweet kornbread
directions: Beat eggs well. Pour cornmeal and sugar into mixing bowl. Blend together. Add beaten eggs; blend with cornmeal and sugar. Add buttermilk to desired thickness.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, onion, eggs, salt, bread crumbs, pepper, seasoning and 1 cup of sauce.
Divide this mixture in half.
Press half in a 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle on the cheese and mushrooms.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Near the end of baking time, spread the rest of the sauce on meat loaf.

title: peanut butter pudding cake
directions: Layer 1:
In small bowl, thoroughly mix 2/3 cup peanuts, flour and softened butter.
Press into bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: hamburger soup
directions: You can add garlic or a little Worcestershire sauce or any other juice or dry onion soup, if you like.

title: nacho pasta skillet
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetable are tender.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: 5 minute meal
directions: This meal takes only 5 minutes to prepare!
Pour all vegetables in a large pan. Cut smoked sausage into bite size pieces and cook on medium until potatoes are soft.

title: spuds
directions: Mix soups, sour cream, onion, cheese, butter, salt and pepper together well. Put into a long baking dish and cook for 45 minutes on 350° or 20 minutes in microwave.
Take out of oven and sprinkle cornflakes on top and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter or oleo in pan.
Add sugar, milk, and cocoa and bring to a roiling boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
