Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Add oats.
Mix well and quick.
Drop on to wax paper and let cool.
Will harden as cookies cool.

title: green beans with mustard
directions: Steam green beans.
Mix Dijon mustard, salt and pepper and lemon.
Whisk in olive oil and toss with the green beans.
Serve hot.

title: tahitian chicken
directions: Cut green pepper into chunks; slice mango or papaya.
Saute chicken in butter or substitute until well browned.
Remove excess fat from pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine syrup, soy sauce, water and garlic and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with ginger and salt.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to heated platter.
Add pineapple, green pepper, green onion, mango or papaya and cherry tomatoes to pan juices.
Stir cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water; add to pan, stirring gently until mixture boils and thickens.
If mixture is not thick enough, stir in 1 additional tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1 tablespoon water. Spoon over chicken.
Serves 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Make sure you have enough ice.
Next, chop mushrooms.
Fry bacon and chop into small bits.
Make second drink and call off work for tomorrow while you can still talk (great idea).
Take Larry's Blend and fold in mushrooms and bacon (easy).
Turn on VH-1.
Turn up volume.
Get buns and cheese ready.
Put burgers on grill.
Keep an eye on them and flip when juice comes through. Turn up VH-1 and hope no one is home next door.
Better make a pitt stop next!
Be sure to refresh you drink (if you can find the vodka).
When juice runs clear (burgers not vodka) they are done. Place on buns with cheese.
Eat, drink and pass out!!!
Then you start over tomorrow.
Next cookbook will contain recipe for "The Perfect Porterhouse."

title: tartar sauce
directions: Add all ingredients to a large mixing bowl.
Mix very well and put in airtight container.
Add dressing to cole slaw, potato salad or macaroni salad.
Remaining dressing keeps well in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, in oven.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Place skin side down in pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn; bake about 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water; add juice of 2 lemons, pineapple juice and ginger ale.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and parsley.
Bring to a boil, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
If too thick, add bouillon or plain water.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extract.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold carefully into batter.
Bake in 10-inch tube.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: complete breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Place in casserole.
Top with layers of cheese and ham.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard in blender. Pour mixture over cheese, ham and bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Take out 2 hours before baking.
Top with cornflakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, flour, salt and vanilla.
Spread 1/4-inch thick in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down with a spoon or fingers.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over bars while still hot. Sprinkle with finely chopped walnuts.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; when done, dice and chill.
Place all ingredients in a bowl and carefully blend in Italian dressing and oregano.

title: french poufs
directions: Combine shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg in bowl, mixing well.
Sift next 4 ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Dip immediately in melted butter and then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: all-purpose cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs with 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Beat in 1/2 cup water, 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Bring sauce to boil over low heat.
Mix well.
Pour over 6 large (1 to 1 1/2-inch thick) pork chops and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake uncovered at 300° until meat is tender.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Pare and thinly slice potatoes.
Toss slices in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Drain.
In crock-pot, put in a slice of ham.
Arrange a layer of potatoes, onion rings, salt, pepper, flour and cheese.
Add next layer same as the first until gone. Sprinkle with remaining flour.
Add butter and undiluted soup. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
Add somemore cheese, if you like, about 30 minutes before serving.
Cheez Whiz is also a good cheese to use with this.

title: double treat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat together margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape into balls, using 1 tablespoon of dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: key lime pie
directions: Pour into 9-inch graham cracker pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight.
If preferred, pie may be baked at 350° for 8 minutes. Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: surprise spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise and spread over a 12-inch platter.
Next, layer with cocktail sauce and sprinkle seafood over the top.
Layer the cheese, green onion and tomatoes over the shrimp.
Cover and chill.

title: round steak potato scallop
directions: Shake flour and round steak in plastic bag until coated.
Brown in 3 tablespoons shortening.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons flour, salt, pepper, thyme and garlic powder.
Pour water over. Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until tender.
Slice potatoes and layer over meat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 450° or until potatoes are tender.

title: georgia barbecue
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Beef or pork may be used but this is an excellent way to use venison.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn first.
In a 2-quart pan combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, stirring constantly.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes or immediately form into balls.
Store in airtight container as soon as cool.

title: spiced molasses cookies
directions: Mix shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Add egg and molasses; mix well.
Combine flour and dry ingredients.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Tops will crack.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake first 3 ingredients in a plastic bag.
Drop into greased Bundt pan.
Melt and pour over remaining 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes.
Pull apart with fingers and eat.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine sauce, sausage and half the pepperoni.
Heat in microwave until bubbly.
Add pasta and heat again.
Top with cheese and pepperoni and heat until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with extra cheese and serve.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Spoon rice into greased casserole.
Cover rice with broccoli. Mix in a bowl 2 tablespoons of butter and bread crumbs.
In frying pan, cook onions in remaining butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add ham.
Heat one minute.
Pour over broccoli casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tacos
directions: Combine ground beef and green pepper in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole; cover.
Microwave at cook stage for 6 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in tomato paste and seasonings; cover.
Microwave for 6 to 9 minutes or until mixture bubbles, stirring once.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Divide mixture between taco shells.
Over meat, top with cheese, then tomato, onion and lettuce.

title: summer slush
directions: Put ingredients into giant canister and fill with water to make 2 gallons.
Freeze until slushy.

title: old-time tomato and onion salad
directions: Choose red ripe tomatoes; wash, peel and wash onion.
Slice tomatoes in half crosswise and onion paper thin.
Arrange slices alternately in a large bowl or on individual salad plates.
Serve with a drizzle of dressing.

title: holiday date nut squares
directions: Simmer fruits in water 5 minutes.
Stir in butter; let cool. Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pork tortilla soup
directions: Brown pork and onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients except tortillas and garnishes.
Simmer, covered, 45 to 60 minutes or until pork is tender.
Cut tortillas into wedges and carefully stir into soup.
Serve with garnishes of grated cheese, yogurt or sour cream, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: hobo packs
directions: Make hamburger patties.
Place a slice of potato, onion and slice of carrot on top of hamburger patty.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Great for on the grill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients and put into loaf pan.
Bake
minutes.
Drain grease.
Bake until done, approximately 20 more minutes.
Serve with my Easy Potatoes!

title: triple cranberry sauce
directions: Combine juice concentrate and sugar in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add fresh and dried berries and cook until dried berries begin to soften and fresh berries begin to pop, stirring often, about 7 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in marmalade, juice and peel and allspice. Cool completely. Cover; chill until cold. Can be made 3 days ahead. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
De-shell Spanish peanuts and add to broccoli, raisins and onion.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and wine vinegar and stir mixture into broccoli.
Chill, toss and enjoy!

title: party punch
directions: Mix all
together, chill and serve with a few ice cubes in each
punch
cup.
Recipe
can
be	doubled or tripled very easily with very good results.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter; beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tortilla torte(mexican)
directions: Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Stir in 2 cups of sour cream.
Cool.
Lay 1 tortilla on a plate and spread with chocolate mixture.
Repeat until all tortillas are used.
Top last layer with sour cream, mixed with 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
(Can be frozen at this point.)
Before serving, top with whipping cream and shaved chocolate or toasted almonds.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. This makes an elegant looking dessert, especially as an ending to a Mexican meal.
Nobody can tell that the thin pastry layers are tortillas.

title: spice tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store.
Mix with hot water.

title: sausage roll
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and mix. Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick; spread with sausage.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Repeat for second.
Roll, wrap and chill.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake in a 400° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain and rinse with water. While beef is cooking, follow directions on box for rice.
After rice is done, put rice, beef, tomato juice, salt, pepper and picante sauce in a large pan and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: brazillian fried rice
directions: *add oil to pan using medium heat.

title: salami triangles
directions: Combine all ingredients except salami; spread mixture on 4 slices of salami.
Stack these.
Top with unspread slice.
You end up with 2 stacks of 5 slices each.
Repeat.
Wrap each stack in wax paper.
Refrigerate.
Cut each into 6 wedges.
Top with pickled onion with toothpick.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple.
Save juice to add to milk to make 1 cup.
Beat eggs and sugar; add juice.
Pour over bread pieces.
Dribble butter over this mixture.
Bake in 350° oven in a 2-quart casserole dish for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine or butter on low heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Pour in whipping cream, stirring continuously until it thickens; set aside.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, lightly stir peas, pimento and egg while adding cream mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove; top with cheese; return back to oven for 10 minutes.
Prep time:
30 minutes.

title: conch stew
directions: Conch must be tenderized before cooking. You have to beat 'em to eat 'em.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Soak All-Bran in sour cream for 30 minutes.
Cream together Crisco, egg, sugar and molasses.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add flour and salt.
Stir into bran mixture.
Add raisins and nutmeats.
Bake in cans, 1/2 to 2/3 full, for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned water until tender.
Remove.
Cool. Debone then return to broth.
Add carrot and potato; cook until tender.
Then add noodles and top with the uncooked dumplings spooned on dumplings

title: gallagher's cheddar cheese soup
directions: Place water in pot over high heat.
Add carrots, celery and green onions; boil 5 minutes and set aside (do not drain).
Melt butter in soup pot over medium heat; saute white onion 1 minute; add flour, blending well.
In a large sauce pan bring milk and broth to a boil.
Whisk broth mixture into flour and onion mixture.
Stir in cheese, salt, pepper, cayenne and mustard.
Add cooked vegetables, including the water in which they were cooked. Bring to a boil, stirring to blend well and serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix soup with about a half can of chicken broth from boiled chicken and pour over chicken. Crush crackers and sprinkle over chicken.
Melt oleo and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake until topping is golden brown, about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: dolly lister's mizette
directions: Brown bell pepper, medium onion, hamburger and sausage together.
Drain. Add together in large bowl the hamburger mixture, mushroom soup, tomato soup, tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic salt, celery flakes and salt and pepper.
Add cooked noodles. Stir together.
Put into casserole dishes (enough for two). Put Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
I have frozen one casserole dish to use later.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Mix egg, vanilla and fruit cocktail together and combine all ingredients.
Pour mixture into two buttered pans.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Place in oven at 325° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 275° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve cold with whipped cream. It is better made the same day as served.

title: country fries
directions: In large skillet, pour 2 tablespoons leftover bacon drippings or cooking oil.
Turn heat up to high.
Dump in all of the ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Once everything starts frying well, turn heat to medium or medium-low.
Cover with lid and let cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Must be stirred, flipped or turned frequently.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions, using oil, eggs and substituting evaporated milk for water.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake according to package directions. Remove from oven.
Top with marshmallows, chocolate morsels and nuts if desired.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes or just until topping is warmed and begins to melt.
Cool for 20 to 30 minutes before cutting.

title: diane's bacon gravy
directions: Fry bacon in a frying pan.
Keep 3 tablespoons of the bacon drippings.
Mix the flour and milk together; add to the drippings. Stir to thicken.

title: beet and walnut salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk together vinegar and oil.
Toss in beets until well coated, then add cheese and walnuts.
Toss gently until just coated.
Line serving platter with green leaf lettuce.
Serve on beet-cheese mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, add 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas, butter and milk.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended and stir in nuts.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Place round steak in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over steak.
Layer onion, potatoes (quartered), carrots, salt and pepper.
Cover top with more barbecue sauce. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes.

title: lemon or orange tea cookies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients together. Add liquid ingredients gradually to this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add brown and white sugar and butter.
Stir until butter melts. Add eggs.
Stir well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Add 1/2 package chocolate pieces.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and remaining chocolate pieces on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cake is so rich it requires no frosting.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender with 2-inches of tops left on.
To pickle beets, use a granite pan large enough to make 8-quarts. Heat all ingredients to a boiling point, then all the cut up beets and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to medium.
Have jars and lids hot.
Fill jars and seal.
Wait 2 weeks before opening for better flavor.

title: original pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs separately; beat well. Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and mace.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. Frost with butter icing.

title: pizza pie crust
directions: Add 1 cup of water to yeast (more if needed).
Add ingredients and stir.
Let dough rise 1 hour.
Makes 2 large pies.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Use any kind of sauce and toppings.

title: chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips, in cream canister.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Freeze as directed. Add chocolate chips immediately after freezing.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 quarts.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour
1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding and mix.
Beat 1 or 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices. Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.

title: pizza bubble casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger.
Put the biscuits in 2 cake pans or 1 large pan.
Put hamburger mixture on biscuits. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Whip cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.

title: lace cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix all ingredients.	Drop by 1/2 teaspoon
onto
foil
lined
baking sheet, 2 inches apart (batter will
spread).
Bake in 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes. Check after 7 minutes.	Watch for edges to turn golden.
Allow to cool on foil.
Peel off foil when completely cool.	(Recipe makes a lot of cookies.)

title: italian chicken
directions: Beat eggs; add salt, pepper and oregano.
Dip chicken in egg, then breadcrumbs.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken on both sides.
Place chicken in 13X9 baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pork chops with turnips
directions: Brown chops in a little onion after you dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Cook until tender.
Cook about 4 good-size turnips with 4 good-size potatoes.
Mash.
Pour grease from chops in turnips and potatoes.

title: delicious strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie crust with 1 quart unsweetened strawberries. Boil water, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch until clear.
Add strawberry jello and red food coloring; cool.
Pour over the strawberries.
Spread whipped cream or Cool Whip on top.
Decorate with berries.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Grease large container; put dough in and turn to grease top.
Cover with foil; let stand overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Next morning, punch down and divide into 3 parts.
Knead each part on a floured surface 8 to 10 times.
Put in greased loaf pans; brush with oil.
Cover with waxed paper; let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Brush top with melted butter.
Can be frozen.
If putting bread in pans on workday to rise, it can set all day.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: quick chicken and biscuits
directions: Put biscuits in an ungreased 10-inch baking dish.
Combine other 3 ingredients and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until biscuits brown.
(They will rise to the top during baking.)
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: caesar's fish
directions: Arrange
fillets in a single layer in a lightly greased 9
x 13-inch
baking
dish.
Drizzle
dressing
over fillets. Sprinkle crumbs
over
top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and
bake
an
additional 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily. Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until softened. Add the remaining ingredients. Cover skillet and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes. Add shrimp and simmer for 10 minutes. Thicken mixture with cornstarch. Serve with white rice.

title: best-ever orange cake
directions: Place egg whites in large bowl and bring to room temperature, about an hour.
Measure sifted flour into bowl and set aside. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup of the granulated sugar, beating after each addition.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.

title: okra and tomatoes(country style)
directions: Fry bacon crispy and set to drain on paper towels. Fry cut okra in bacon grease, adding onions to saute. Add the whole tomatoes (mashed), the crisp bacon (crumbled) and the seasonings. Let simmer for about 30 minutes, adding a little water when needed.

title: miss betty's cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Roll each piece in melted butter, then in brown sugar/white sugar mixture.
Place in pie pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts or parsley.

title: stir-fried beef
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut with grain into 2-inch strips.
Cut strips across into 1/8-inch slices.
Toss beef in vegetable oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, salt, sugar, soy sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.

Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat. Without stirring, cook over low heat (small to medium bubbles breaking across surface of liquid) until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 266° or small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a hard ball which doesn't flatten until pressed, about 40 minutes.
When temperature reaches 260°, in a large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Beating at high speed, gradually add hot syrup in a thin, steady stream.
DO NOT SCRAPE SIDE OF SAUCEPAN.
Continue beating at high speed until mixture begins to lose its gloss, about 3 minutes.

title: potato supreme
directions: Pressure potatoes and grate (potatoes need to be firm and not mushy or they will be hard to grate).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: creamy hot sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use as a dipping sauce for bite size chicken pieces, cooked, French fries or tortilla chips.

title: maple-glazed chicken wings
directions: Cut off wingtips and discard; cut wings in half at joint. Stir together syrup and next 5 ingredients; reserve 1 cup mixture and chill.	Place chicken in a heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag; pour remaining syrup mixture over chicken.	Seal and chill 4 hours, turning chicken occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade, discarding marinade.
Grill chicken, without grill lid, over medium-high (350° to 400°) for 30 minutes or until done, turning and basting occasionally with reserved 1 cup syrup mixture.
Yields 8 appetizer servings.

title: "snick snack"
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix ingredients and put mixture on individual pieces of party rye bread.
Heat in oven and serve.

title: blueberry rolls
directions: Roll biscuits together into oblong shape and butter.
Mix flour, berries, sugar and lemon juice.
Arrange berries on dough and roll up.
Seal ends.
Bake in hot oven 450° about 20-25 minutes until brown.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in crock, large enough to cover with liquid.
Cover with the following mixture: 1 part vinegar to 3 parts water, then add all other ingredients.
After 2 or 3 days, drain meat.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender in
4 to 5 tablespoons butter or broth.
Add chicken broth and pepper and simmer for 30 minutes. Blend flour, milk, cheese and parsley into a smooth sauce and add to broth.
Cook, stirring, until thick and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: moms turkey dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuits and stuffing mix together. Saute celery, onion in margarine; add to bread mixture.
Cut up cooked giblets fine, add to bread.
Add salt and pepper, eggs to bread, mix together.
Add soup, sage, chicken seasoning, milk and hot pepper, mix well.
Bake at 350° until brown about 25-35 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Stir in bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and Old Bay seasoning.
Shape mixture into 4-ounce cakes and pan-fry until golden brown.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake 2 (8-inch or 9-inch) cakes; let cool completely.
In small bowl, mix together vanilla pudding, milk and sour cream. Mix well and chill 1 hour.
In large bowl, mix strawberry jello and boiling water, then add in pie glaze and frozen strawberries. Mix well and chill 1 hour.

title: quick made cinnamon rolls
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch pan, mix melted margarine and 1 cup brown sugar, covering bottom of pan.
Cover either with almonds, pecans or chopped walnuts.
Place rolls in rows to fit nicely in pan.
In separate pan or bowl, mix pudding mix (dry), 1/2 cup brown sugar and about a teaspoon of cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of rolls; cover with wax paper and let sit at room temperature overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 50 minutes.
Turn upside down on foil.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, sugar and pecans.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes; cool.

title: flank steak
directions: Marinate steak 24 hours at room temperature.
Cook on grill or in broiler about 7 minutes a side (well done or crispy on the outside).

title: taboulee salad
directions: Mix water and bulgar together to moisten.
Saute onion and oil. Add to bulgar.
Set aside.
Mix together green onion, parsley and bell pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add bulgur mixture.
Mix well, refrigerate and let stand 15 minutes or more. Serve.

title: fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in bits until melted.
Add rest of ingredients until blended.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Chill.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Wash and cut in half.
Remove seeds.
Bake, cut side down, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn cut side up.
Fill cavity with butter and honey or brown sugar.
Continue baking for 20 minutes more or until done.

title: caesar deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise in half with rippled vegetable cutter or sharp knife. Carefully remove yolks and place in a small bowl; reserve egg white halves.

title: lasagne
directions: Prepare meat balls and spaghetti sauce as directed in preceding recipes.
Cook all 24 meat balls in thick spaghetti sauce.
Cook lasagne noodles in salted boiling water until firm (not too done).
Add cold water to stop cooking.
Drain.

title: stollen
directions: Unroll the dough, to make a large rectangle onto a greased cookie sheet.
Spread with softened cream cheese (heated briefly in microwave).
Sprinkle over raisins, cinnamon and sugar.
Lifting the long edge of the rectangle, bring edge to center.
Join with opposite edge (of long side of rectangle) in the center by pinching dough.
Pinch short ends, also (so filling doesn't run out).

title: pizza fish fillets(low-fat)
directions: Cut fish into 6 serving size pieces.
Spray rectangular baking dish with nonstick spray coating.
Measure the thickness of fish. Place fish in prepared baking dish, tucking under the thin edges. Sprinkle with the lemon pepper.
Bake fish, uncovered, in a 450° oven for 6 to 9 minutes per 1/2 inch of thickness.

title: broccoli cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray 2 (12-cup) muffin tins with Pam cooking spray. Fill cups about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
You may easily cut this recipe in half and make 12 muffins.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grate some cheese on top.
Cook for 15 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.

title: beer battered fish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add oil and fold in beaten egg whites.
Dip fish in batter and fry in oil until golden brown. Good luck!

title: impossible pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle pecans in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Slightly oil 1 mold or Bundt cake pan.
Set aside.
Cook shrimp, soup and cream cheese (until smooth) over medium heat. Remove from fire.
Add celery and onions.
Stir.
Melt gelatine in water per package directions.
Add to shrimp mixture.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt oleo, then melt peanut butter with it and bring to a boil.
Add powdered sugar and stir thoroughly.
Put in buttered 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator until hard; cut to size you desire.

title: delicious pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water. Cool a few minutes. Add jello to mayonnaise a little at a time until blended. Stir in remaining ingredients. Add pinch of salt. Place in covered dish. Refrigerate. Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: texas bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Arrange cheese in criss-cross fashion on top of beans.
Bake until cheese melts. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix well with a mixer and put into a greased casserole.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer until ingredients thicken, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.

title: vegetable platter
directions: Peel carrots.
Cut in half crosswise and quarter lengthwise. Snap beans and cut in half.
Cut roots of leeks and remove coarse outer leaves.
Cut off all but 2 inches of the green tops.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Place chicken broth in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add green beans and return to boiling.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add leeks and carrots; return to simmer and cook, covered, 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Arrange on platter.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water in small pan for 5 minutes. Dissolve over hot water until liquid.
Add 1/4 cup sour cream gradually to be dissolved with gelatin.
Stir to blend.
Add to remaining sour cream with onion and salt and mix thoroughly. Cover tightly, chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, fluff up with fork and fold in crumbled bacon.

title: heavenly rice dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 3/4 cup juice.
Bring the juice to a boil. Stir in instant rice and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let steam 5 minutes.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Fold marshmallows into hot pudding. Add pineapple, pecans and rice. Chill. Garnish with whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Place frozen potatoes and onions in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
In a small bowl soften cream cheese by microwaving 30 to 40 seconds.
Stir in soup.
Stir mixture into potatoes.
Cover casserole and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until center is hot.
Stir once during cooking.
Top with shredded cheese and let stand 5 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Pour boiling water on raisins.
Let cool.
Cream sugar with shortening.
Add egg, vanilla and molasses.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Grease 4 (No. 2) tin cans.
Fill each can half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink. Stir to break meat into pieces.
Drain. Stir in sauce.
Cover dish and microwave until mixture boils.

title: easy basil potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes; cut into 2-inch cubes (leave skins on).
Put potatoes and all other ingredients into a microwavable cooking dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 10 to 14 minutes, mixing ingredients halfway through.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in loaf pan.

title: lacy corn meal pancakes
directions: Mix corn meal, baking soda and salt together. Add beaten egg and buttermilk, beating until smooth. The secret of getting the cakes trimmed with lace is to get the batter thin.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a large pot.
Boil and stir 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour in greased pan.

title: chicken and cheese strata
directions: Pour egg mixture over bread, cheese and chicken layers. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick "no rise" bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Grease a loaf pan and pour batter into it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper. Lightly grease miniature (or regular) muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden. Remove from tins; place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: strawberry salsa
directions: In bowl, combine strawberries, green pepper, onions and parsley.
Stir in salad dressing and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken spaghetti(serves 10)
directions: Cook chicken with onion, bay leaf and salt.
Chill, bone and chop.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Use 2 tablespoons of chicken broth.
Add flour, salt, pepper, 1 cup chicken broth and 1 cup milk for white sauce.
Dice celery, onions, pimentos and green pepper.
Add cheese.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in a shallow pan.
Cover with buttered crumbs or potato chips.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Let first 5 ingredients stand 3 hours in ice water; drain well.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil and then pour over cucumbers which are packed in the jars.
Cold pack for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil and chunk chicken (save broth).
Mix soups, tomatoes and chilies in blender.
Add chicken and heat slowly until hot, through and through.

title: creamy strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells and chill.

title: italian pinwheels
directions: Bring tortillas to room temperature.
Soften cream cheese in microwave for 1 minute. Combine cream cheese and pesto. Spread the mixture over the surface of each tortilla.
Scatter chopped peppers over cream cheese.
Cover cheese and peppers with thin slices of salami, dividing the meat evenly among the tortillas. Roll each tortilla tightly into a tube.
Use plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: english trifle
directions: You simply put this together in layers:

title: fruit freeze
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add drained fruit and nuts, mixing carefully.
Add whipped cream.
Put in ice tray and freeze approximately 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake with lime glaze
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature. Position rack in lower third of oven and preheat to 325°. Grease and flour a fleur-de-lis (Bundt or other) cake pan. Over a sheet of waxed paper, sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer meat mixture, shredded Cheddar cheese and corn tortillas, ending with meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: To eggs, add next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° until firm. Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven just long enough to melt.

title: hoffman's crockpot meatloaf
directions: Mix all together.
Should be very moist.
(add more milk if needed).
Shape and place in crockpot.

title: vegetarian pasta
directions: Cut pepper into strips; slice carrots diagonally and cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Stir-fry in olive oil (1 tablespoon) until just tender.
(Cook each vegetable separately). Mix vegetables and cooked pasta together.
Add 1 clove crushed garlic, 2 tablespoons olive oil and squeeze a lemon wedge into mixture; stir and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and chopped fresh parsley.

title: dutchess potatoes
directions: If frozen, thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well. Add rhubarb, lemon rind, eggs, oil and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use juice of lemon and powdered sugar for glaze.
Spread on cake while still warm.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in all other ingredients with a spoon; do not beat.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting:

title: goody bars
directions: Combine the first three ingredients.
Spread mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Spread mixture over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: dessert
directions: Mix cake mix and bake 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Time for cake is approximate.
Check for doneness.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese according to directions on pudding.
Spread on cake.
Then spread pineapple on pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Spread on pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: ham quiche
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in plate.
Blend rest of ingredients and pour over.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: salmon loaf with cheese sauce
directions: Flake salmon; mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with Cheese Sauce.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon melts
directions: Cream 1 cup soft margarine.
Add 1/3 cup confectioners sugar, 3/4 cup cornstarch and 1 cup plain flour.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown on bottom, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot tomato pan bread
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients; mix until well blended. Pour batter into preheated 9-inch cake pan coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread tests done with toothpick.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.
Serve warm. Yields 10 servings.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: In a small pan, combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted and smooth.
Spread over cake.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, 3/4 cups sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour batter into a 10 x 8-inch pan.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Carefully pour water on top.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares and turn upside down to serve.

title: susie chew brownies
directions: Cook on low heat or in microwave the caramels and 1/3 cup or little more of the evaporated milk until caramels are melted. Meanwhile, mix together cake mix, margarine and 2 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Add pecans to this.
Take half of dough and spread in 9 x 11-inch pan ungreased.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°. Spread chocolate chips over dough, then spread caramel mixture. Take remaining cake dough and sprinkle over top.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cut when cool.

title: ez tater soup
directions: Cook potatoes in small amount of water with chopped onion. When about done, add soups.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir the meat, onions and bell pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper; heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk, Cool Whip and sour cream.
Put layer of wafers in a large dish or pan, layer of bananas and cover with pudding mixture.
Continue with layers until all the mixture is used.
Top with crushed wafers or cookies.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet until done.
Mix tomatoes, tomato paste and water all together in large pan.
Add kidney beans and rest of ingredients.
Coffee is optional.
Simmer 2 hours.
Enjoy with crackers, fruit and dessert.

title: thimbleberry fritters
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add sugar, egg yolks and water.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites stiff, then fold into flour mixture along with berries.
Drop dough from a tablespoon into hot (365°) deep oil.
Fry until fritters are golden brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes 12.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Brown beef tips.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Make a flour gravy; add to crock-pot.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and Lipton onion soup mix to gravy and beef tips.
Cook in crock-pot for 6 to 7 hours on medium setting.
Serve over rice.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil, then cut to a simmer. Pack the cukes in jars; add the rest of ingredients.
Pour liquid over cukes in jar and seal.
Put in hot water bath in canner of boiling water and let it set for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not cook in canner, just let it sit in water.

title: chicken curry
directions: Fry onions in butter.
Add flour, salt, curry powder and chicken stock.
Stir constantly until mixture is thick.
Add milk, lemon juice and chicken.
Heat well.
(May be made in advance and reheated.)
Serve over rice with chopped bacon or chutney, diced pineapple and coconut.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey and asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus and turkey in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine the next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon mixture over turkey.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crispy coated chicken
directions: Crush soup mix in pouch.
Combine soup mix, bread crumbs and pepper.
Beat together egg and water.
Dip chicken into egg mixture; coat with crumb mixture.
On baking sheet, arrange chicken.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serves 6.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place bread slices in greased casserole.
Cook sausage until slightly brown; drain.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs and half and half.
Pour over cheese.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (until set).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot cranberry apple casserole
directions: Wash cranberries and place in casserole.
Lay apple slices over cranberries.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients and spread over cranberry/apple mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown. (Use of microwave to cook mixture will decrease cooking time. Place in oven under broiler until brown, if using microwave.)

title: pineapple praline cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, eggs and juice (if not enough juice, add water to make 1 1/3 cups).
Pour half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour crushed pineapple over mixture.
Then cover with remaining batter.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.
Then take praline mixture (butter, brown sugar, pecans and coconut) and spread over cake.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 5 tablespoons warm water; set aside.
Sift together dry ingredients, then cut shortening into the mixture. Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to the dry ingredients and shortening.
Stir by hand until somewhat sticky.
Put on floured board.
Roll out with floured rolling pin and cut biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown or golden.
Makes 25 large biscuits.
Will store in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Drain.
Add chili and seasonings.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Heat through.
Serve hot with corn chips (Doritos, Tostitos).
For more spicy dip, use Velveeta cheese with jalapeno peppers.

title: nan millar's shortbread
directions: Knead together
until
dough
forms a ball and does not stick to
fingers.
Must knead by hand and have butter at room temperature.
Divide into two equal portions and pat each into a small
pie pan (ungreased).
Prick top with a fork.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Done when light brown on top.
Makes 2 gift-size.

title: chicken bundles italian
directions: Bone, skin and coarsely chop chicken (1 1/2 cups).
In large skillet, cook chicken and onion in hot oil over medium heat, until chicken is no longer pink.

In a large mixing bowl, combine partially thawed and drained spinach, cheeses, spices and lemon juice; stir in chicken and onion and add salt and pepper to taste. Lightly butter 8 (10 ounce) custard cups or a muffin pan.
Line each with an egg roll wrapper and spoon in chicken mixture in equal amounts in each cup.
Fold the ends of each wrapper over the chicken mixture and seal to make a bundle; brush with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until tops are golden. Loosen bundles with knife and remove from cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift cake mix on top.
Grate butter over top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until browned.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook onion in a small amount of olive oil or water.
Mix to all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or in microwave on High until done.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients, make into meatballs, roll in flour and fry in a little oil until done.
When done, put in a container and add the rest of the sweet 'n sour sauce.
It's best if eaten the next day.
Warm on the stove or in the microwave--Enjoy!!

title: spicy blueberry pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients, toss gently.
Fit 1 pie crust into 9 inch pie plate according to pkg directions.
Spoon blueberry mixture into pie shell.
Cover with remaining pie crust, fold and crimp edges.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Cut crust to vent.

title: meatballs with bacon
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Form into balls.
Moisten with egg and milk mixture.
Wrap in bacon.
Fasten bacon with toothpick.
Bake in hot oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Pour marshmallow cream into mixing bowl.
In heavy saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, then cook at medium heat until soft ball stage.
Pour mixture into marshmallow cream slowly while stirring.
Beat by hand until candy forms peaks.
Add pecans and spoon out on waxed paper.

title: bird's nest pudding
directions: Let fruit come to a boil.
Mix together sugar, butter, egg, flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Drop by large spoons on the boiling fruit.
Put in oven and bake until rich brown.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil; beat at medium speed 2 minutes or until well blended.
Add the egg and beat until light and lemon colored.
On low speed of the mixer, add the flour mixture alternately with the banana, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in the vanilla. Pour the batter into a bread pan coated with vegetable cooking spray; bake it at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 16 servings at 120 calories per 1/2 inch slice.
Protein 2.1 g, fat 4 g, carbohydrate 19.4 g, cholesterol 17 g, iron 5 g, sodium 93 g and calcium 17 g.

title: fried plantains
directions: Peel plantain banana and cut into 1/2-inch slices at a 45° angle.
Pour enough cooking oil in a frying pan to cover 1/2 of the slices.
Heat cooking oil on medium heat.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and powdered sugar for crust. Press into pizza pan (optional).
For crust, Pillsbury sugar cookie dough can be used.

title: banana loaf and icing
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add all other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 14-inch loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in ice water and lemon juice.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Fold in cranberry sauce, celery and walnuts.
Pour all this into a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tater delights
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper and spread in baking dish.
Top with mushroom soup and pour Cheddar cheese over this and top with Tater Tots.
Bake until brown.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine sugar
and
oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, alternately with buttermilk and blend well.
Add vanilla. Fold in chopped nuts and prunes. Pour into greased pan and bake at 300° about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In large bowl, put sugar, flour and salt.
In heavy small pan, bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Take cocoa mixture from heat as soon as it boils and add immediately to dry ingredients.
Add sour cream.
Add eggs and soda, mixing until well blended after each addition.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in a greased cookie sheet type pan with high sides or 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: One day in advance before serving, mix well all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers coarsely into pastry-lined plate.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in a saucepan and boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Pour syrup over crackers. Dot generously with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions omitting salt; drain.
Combine macaroni and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray; sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings (about 158 calories per serving).

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Boil, debone and dice the chicken.
Mix chicken with next 6 ingredients.
Fill and roll mixture into tortillas.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour remainder of sauce over casserole.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until hot through and cheese begins to brown.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Combine raisins in water and simmer for 15 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Add beaten egg.
Add soft shortening, oats, sweetener and flavoring.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix all together well.
Pour into greased one-layer cake pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Yields an 8-inch cake.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill bowl and beaters.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water; set in refrigerator.
When mixture has partially congealed, fold in the Pet milk which has been whipped with a beater.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Pour in Jell-O mixture; cover with more crumbs and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well.
Combine evaporated milk and cream; heat to scalding point then add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
If smaller shells are used, bake longer.
Pie is done when knife inserted near rim comes out clean.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Place sprig of dill in bottom of sterile jar.
Pack cucumbers in jar.
Pour boiling brine over pickles and seal.
Wait at least 6 weeks to use.

title: poor man's salami
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix again and refrigerate another 24 hours.
Roll and shape into loaves.
Bake 8 hours at 150° to 175° on a broiler pan.

title: oreo cookie jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Measure 1 3/4 cups Jell-O into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Chill 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Just before serving, slice bananas and add to mixture.
Stir and serve.

title: vodka-russel refresher
directions: Mix vodka and juice.
Freeze, stirring frequently.
When icy, place 1 scoop in a glass.
Fill with Squirt.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
(I dice the cheese so it will melt faster.) Stir often. This can be cooked in crock-pot or microwave.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients except cinnamon stick.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Serve hot with twist of orange peel and cinnamon stick.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add celery, onion and rice.
Let simmer until tender, stirring occasionally.
Boil cabbage for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Mix mushroom soup and meat mixture together with the milk.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spread cabbage on bottom. Then spread the mushroom mixture over cabbage.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes with a lid over it, then remove lid, add cheese and bake for 15 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: rachel's herbed veal with wine
directions: Trim excess fat from veal.
Cut veal into 1-inch strips and dredge in flour.
Saute veal in butter and olive oil in large skillet until lightly browned.
Remove veal to 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute onions in pan drippings until tender.
Stir in chicken broth and next 5 ingredients.
Mix well and pour over veal.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain and save liquid.
Break corned beef in tiny bits. Put corned beef, pepper, onion and potatoes in a baking dish.
Mix milk, flour and potato liquid until smooth.
Pour over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Season meat with salt, pepper and parsley. Cook manicotti in 4 quarts of water for 8 to 10 minutes. Drain in a bowl, combine milk and egg. Moisten the bread slices. Tear and mix with meat. Stuff in manicotti. Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over manicotti. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: quick lunch casserole
directions: Mix mac and chili, cover with cheese and bake in oven at 350 degrees until hot through and cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream (optional).

title: rita's crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter; stir in cornstarch.
Add onions, garlic and green pepper.
Cook until onions are done.
Add the fat.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add crawfish tails and cook additional 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
If desired, add 1/3 can of Ro-Tel tomatoes to mixture.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Break pretzels and place on cookie sheet.
Pour sauce over pretzels.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: dog food sandwiches
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger; drain well.
Add Velveeta cheese in chunks.
Combine garlic and oregano to mixture.
Spread on party rye.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties.
Dip each patty into evaporated milk and then into crushed cracker crumbs or corn flakes.
Fry until golden brown on each side.

title: homemade peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Take milk and sugar and mix together for thickening.
Then take 1/2 stick butter and dissolve and pour into the thickening.
Pour thickening into large baking pan.
Take the peaches and stir into thickening.
Take the other 1/2 stick of butter and cut over the mixture.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown everything but the soup.
Add soup; mix well and put into a casserole and top with Tater Tots.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Puree ingredients in blender.
Chill and serve over boiled shrimp.

title: egg nog(my father's from his father to me)
directions: Separate yolks from whites; beat yolks until light.
Blend with sugar, whipping cream, milk and salt.
Mix well with the whiskey, rum and brandy.
Let stand, covered, under refrigeration overnight.
Then beat whites of eggs until stiff, not dry; fold lightly into mixture.
Sprinkle grated nutmeg on top.
Will keep for weeks.

title: beef taco casserole
directions: Place corn chips in greased baking dish. Mix taco seasoning with meat and pour over chips. Spoon beans over beef and bake at 350°F. for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top. Place back in oven for 5 minutes. Remove and garnish with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: dutch triple fudge cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding as directed.
Blend in devil's food cake mix (dry mix).
Pour into prepared oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with the chocolate bits and the chopped walnuts. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° (325° if glass pan is used).

title: babicka's babovka
directions: Grate rind into the bottom of the mixing bowl.
Cream with sugar and butter.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks and vanilla to mixture.
Sift salt and baking powder into flour.
The five flour siftings are essential for the resultant final texture.
Then alternately combine sifted flour and milk with the creamed mixture. Beat egg whites and gently cut them in.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Hoska crumbs may also be sprinkled in.
Chopped walnuts if desired are then sprinkled in.
Gently pour in the mixture and bake for about 45 minutes or until done in a 375° oven.
Cool before removing from pan to serve.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Let stand overnight.
Bring to a good boil; boil 1 minute. Take from stove and put in jello.
Stir until well dissolved. Seal while hot.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients and add to the casserole dish. Stir thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with grated cheese while still hot.

title: talerine
directions: Brown onion in little fat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Save a little cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: enchiladas with "refried" beans and two sauces
directions: In a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook 3 to 4 minutes until softened.
Add chili powder and oregano; cook and stir 1 minute. To mixture in skillet, add beans, corn, broth, cilantro, salt and pepper; bring to boil, stirring.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid has been absorbed.

title: mamye johnston icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a graham cracker pie crust. Let set in refrigerator for about 1 hour to set.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, mixing well. Combine salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, stirring well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chow mein
directions: In 3-quart glass casserole stir together soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir in chestnuts, bean sprouts and mushrooms, then meat, celery and onion.
Microwave on High 20 to 22 minutes, stirring well after 10 minutes, until hot and thickened.
Stir thoroughly and serve over chow mein noodles or cooked rice.

title: sweet salad
directions: Tear lettuce.
Mix lettuce with pineapple and bananas.
Mix salad dressing with sugar.
Pour over lettuce.
Mix thoroughly.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in buttered pie plate (large) at 350°
for 45 minutes or until set.

title: souped up potatoes
directions: Mix soups and sour cream together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and line with hash browns, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes, cover with cheese and cornflakes; dot with oleo.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pot roast
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, 1/2 of salt and pepper.
Coat roast with mixture.
In Dutch oven, in oil, brown roast evenly on all sides.
Remove roast from oven.
Place in oven-safe pot.
Using Dutch oven, cook onions until tender.
Place onions on top of roast.
Add remaining salt and 1 1/4 cups water.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes more, until meat and vegetables are tender.
Mix 1/4 cup water with flour mixture on top of stove.
Thicken broth with mixture.
Pour over meat and vegetables.

title: hot clam spread
directions: Combine clams and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Saute mixture of rest of ingredients, except for bread crumbs.
Combine with the clams.
Add bread crumbs.
Spread should be stiff.
Add more crumbs if necessary.
Spread on your favorite crackers.

title: mid-west casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add cabbage, potato, celery, carrot, onion and parsley.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine egg yolks and milk; blend in bread cubes, salt and pepper.
Gradually blend in vegetable mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy cabbage-apple slaw
directions: In medium bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, green pepper, apples and onion (or scallion).
In 1-cup measure or small bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; pour over vegetables and toss until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 4 servings.
This will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Combine caramels and evaporated milk in top of double boiler. Heat until caramels are melted. Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup butter.
Mix well until melted.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar. Cool slightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into a dish of salted peanuts. Form into log. Roll until coated with nuts.
Place on waxed paper. Makes about 50.

title: caroline's manicotti
directions: You will need 2 (12 x 9-inch) casserole dishes and 2 (14 x 12-inch) sheets of foil.
tags: ingredients required for your favorite meat

title: zucchini doughnuts
directions: Mix all together.
Drop in grease at 375° with a doughnut maker.
When cooked on one side, turn.

title: busy day meat loaves
directions: Mix together the beef, eggs, tomato paste, rolled oats, relish, onion soup and onion.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Place in 12 ungreased muffin cups.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 individual meat loaves.

title: meat loaf topping
directions: Combine and spread over top of meat loaf before baking.

title: sugar free cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.
Store in an air tight container.
For each serving add 1/3 cup mix to 3/4 cup boiling water, stir to dissolve.
Yield:
2 2/3 cups mix (8 servings).
Exchanges:
1 milk.
Serving:
1 cup.
Calories:

title: jonathan's pancakes
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add margarine. Makes about twelve 4-inch pancakes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine white cake mix, flour, eggs, oil, water, Jell-O and 1/2 cup frozen strawberries in large bowl and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 350° oven for about 40 minutes. Combine butter, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons crushed strawberries.
Drizzle over warm cake.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Soak crumbs in broth, soup and butter for 15 minutes.
Add eggs and all other ingredients.
You made add chicken pieces, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until golden brown in 10 x 18-inch pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water for 7 minutes.
Add milk and butter, then cook 1 hour on low heat.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and if desired, raisins.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook 1 quart boiling water and raisins 15 or 20 minutes.
Beat egg, sugar, flour, vinegar and cinnamon.
Add to boiling mixture. Cook until thick.
Bake in 2 crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Serve with pineapple chunks, banana chunks, strawberries or any fruit you like.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour pan. Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese danish
directions: Cream sugar, egg, cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Grease cookie sheet and lay 1 package crescent rolls on sheet.
Roll edge up.
Put cream cheese mixture on top. Layer other package crescent rolls on top.
Roll edge.
Brush top with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix orange juice, almond extract, salt and honey.
Pour over dry ingredients and toss together.
Crumble into shallow baking sheets in 3/4-inch layer. Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins after baking.
Makes 14 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute shallots in melted butter in pan and add mushrooms. Continue to saute for 5 minutes, then add chicken broth.
Bring soup to boil and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Pour into blender gradually and mix until smooth.
Return soup to pan; add cream, salt, pepper and sherry.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve very hot.

title: old time corn relish
directions: Chop all vegetables;
mix with mustard, sugar and vinegar in large enamel pot.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Quickly fill jars and seal.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
In a small bowl, mix together sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over bean mixture. Refrigerate overnight in an airtight container.
Drain well before serving.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pie filling as directed.
Pour into dry yellow cake mix.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips and pecans over cake mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; mix wet ingredients.
Combine and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates and set aside to cool.
Cream together sugar, oleo, butter and eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients with date mixture to cream mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato raisin patties
directions: Mash potatoes.
Beat in egg and salt.
Add flour and mix well. Mix in raisins.
Drop mixture from a tablespoon on heated, greased frypan.
Brown slowly on each side.

title: schav(sorrel soup)
directions: Slice potatoes very thin and cook in soup stock until tender. Add onion and cook a few minutes longer, then add sorrel leaves, carefully picked over, washed and finely chopped.
Cook only long enough to wilt.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Beat egg yolks and add slowly to soup.
Add sour cream and serve, sprinkled with minced dill weed.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and drain well.
Then pour hot water over it and drain again.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy and light colored. Mix all ingredients, except rice and raisins.
Pour in casserole dish and stir in rice and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This is creamier if not overcooked.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate before serving. Allow time for flavor to blend, overnight.

title: wilderness pie
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours. Combine Cool Whip with cream cheese and mix well.
Slice banana in bottom of crust.
Pour mixture over bananas and top with cherries.

title: chicken asparagus hot dish
directions: In large 9 x 13-inch pan or 3-quart casserole dish, layer the above ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes of baking, sprinkle chow mein noodles over top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thickened, then add salt, pepper and butter.
Add salad dressing and mustard to taste. Excellent for potato salad.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat Ricotta until smooth, adding 1 1/2 cups sugar and egg yolks, mixing after each addition.
Beat in flour and vanilla. Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold whipped cream and egg whites into Ricotta and put into a 12-inch spring-form pan that already has been buttered and sprinkled with graham cracker crumbs. Bake in 425° oven for first 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and cool in oven with door closed.
Top with fruits.

title: quick and easy cake
directions: Note:
Use applesauce in baking to cut back or cut the fat in the recipe.
To do this, replace some or all of the fat in baking recipes with applesauce.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, brown meat which has been cut into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the bouillon.
Stir in remaining bouillon, ketchup, garlic and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend reserved bouillon and flour.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: heart healthy chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil and margarine in pan on top of stove over medium heat; add chicken pieces and sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt to taste.
Stir-fry until done.
While chicken is cooking, drain the liquid from each vegetable and place vegetables in microwave-safe casserole dish and heat them in microwave for 3 minutes, then drain the accumulated liquid.
Add the vegetable mixture to the cooked rice.
Serve the cooked chicken over the vegetable and rice mixture.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Really quick meal.
Takes less time to prepare than it does to read this recipe!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook in water 9 minutes the broccoli until tender and drain. Mix broccoli, rice and cheese and put in a dish.
Add shredded cheese on top layer.
Add crackers crumbled.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate toffee trifle
directions: Make devil's food cake following instructions on box.
Let cake cool and then cut into 1-inch squares. Mix dry pudding mixture with the milk and kahlua.
Crush frozen Heath bars and put aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets with peelings.
Peel and pack hot in hot sterile jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint.
Heat vinegar, water and sugar to boiling.
Pour over beets.
Seal.

title: frances' green party salad
directions: Place the Jell-O in top of double boiler.
Add the boiling water.
Place the double boiler over hot water.
Stir until Jell-O dissolves.
Add marshmallows and stir until they are completely dissolved.
Add pineapple. Set aside until cool.
Set in refrigerator.
When it begins to congeal, add the cream cheese and Dream Whip that have been whipped together.
Pour into a sheet pan rinsed in cold water.
Refrigerate until set.

title: risengrot
directions: Add rice to 1 1/2 quarts milk.
Cook in double boiler.
Add more milk as needed.
Cook 2 hours.
Stir frequently, every 20 minutes.
Twenty minutes before done, add cinnamon and almond. Serve with pat of butter in center, sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar.
Whoever gets almond has good luck for coming year.
Serve New Year's Eve.

title: mexicana cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs, margarine and onions, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in corn and cheese. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm, 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish, arrange remaining ingredients; pour over potatoes. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: shortbread drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg yolk, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Mix in nuts and drop by small teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until light brown on bottom.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs. Add bananas.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and nuts.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: peppered steak
directions: Use long strips of round steak, put paprika on and let set. Cut peppers in strips.
Cut up green onions and quarter the tomatoes.
Cook rice.
Brown garlic in butter in skillet with meat and cook until brown.
Pour beef broth on steak after browned. Simmer this for 30 minutes.
Add onions and peppers; cook for 10 minutes.
Mix soy sauce, water and cornstarch together and pour on top of skillet; thicken to a clear, brown sauce.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Put over rice and serve.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake in 2 layers (according to directions on package).
Let layers get completely cold.
Split each layer in half to make 4 layers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix the corn bread part; add all other ingredients, except cheese and 1/3 cup oil.
Put this 1/3 cup oil in large skillet and add half of corn bread mixture.
Cover with half the grated cheese; put the remaining corn bread in next and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 375° oven until golden brown and bread is done, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: swiss tagliarini
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except noodles).
Cover.
Cook about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Cook noodles and drain. Add to mixture before serving.
(Stir in grated cheese, if desired.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Chop onion and fry with next 3 ingredients.
Stir sweet milk, salt and pepper to taste. Put in pan and put biscuits on top. Bake quickly.
When biscuits are done, all is done.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, and water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and food color.
Let cool.
Soften cream cheese with 1 Tbsp. milk.
Using a spoon, spread cream cheese all over bottom of cooked pie shell.
Place cut up berries in the pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries. Refrigerate to get cool.
When ready to eat, top with whipped cream or cool whip. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; cool and let almost set.
Add crushed pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat pineapple juice.
Add sugar, flour and beaten egg. Cook until thick; let cool, then fold in whipped cream.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over all.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all and place in baking dish or casserole that has been greased.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 stick melted oleo over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cover the last 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
