directions: Cut peppers lengthwise, remove seeds and wash.
Lightly mix beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1 can tomato sauce.
Fill pepper halves.
Top with cheese and arrange close together in baking dish.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Sift together cake mix and jello; then add water, eggs, oil and orange flavoring. Mix with electric mixer for 3 to 5 minutes, until smooth. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: zesty cheese ball
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together and form a ball. Roll in crushed pecans and refrigerate.

title: jackson bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix bread, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine cranberries, sugar and water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Drain cranberries, reserving the liquid to make the sauce.
Add cranberries, raisins and walnuts to the bread mixture.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart mold and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Add the cornstarch to the reserved liquid and cook until thickened.
Spoon over the pudding when serving.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Layer in 2-inch rectangle dish and refrigerate.

title: sherry chicken
directions: This sauce will marinate 7 to 10 chicken breasts, so I cut it in half a lot.
When grilling, be very careful not to overcook. Ten to 15 minutes for chicken tenders is plenty of time.
I found that when grilling these, the tenders do best.

title: lois' pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla. Add milk, sifted flour, baking powder and salt. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cut out butter cookies
directions: Work sugar, butter, flour and baking powder together.
Then add eggs and baking soda.
Mix with beater.
Chill dough.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes large amount.

title: viva la chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish; let stand 12 hours or overnight.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put into a Pyrex baking dish.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut mixture.

title: hot dish
directions: Combine the hamburger, salt and celery.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; pat into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pudding and spread evenly over cooled crust.
Arrange bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip in order given on top of pudding mixture; spread evenly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8; each serving equals 1 bread, 1/2 protein, 1/2 fat, 1/8 milk, 3/4 fruit and 40 optional.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix orange juice and water together.
Add Hawaiian Punch and ginger ale and mix well.
Put sherbet in and let set for 30 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Brown chopped onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer sauce for 30 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and combine with graham crackers.
Pat into pan to form crust.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.
Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust. Drain pineapple thoroughly in colander.
Spread over sugar mixture.
Slice bananas and arrange over pineapple as next layer. Spread softened Cool Whip as top layer.
Seal edges.
May garnish with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: aunt fudie's devilish food cake
directions: Pour 1 cup cold water over all.
Mix well with fork.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: katie's mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados with lemon juice.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Spread picante sauce over avocados. Mix refried beans with a few tablespoons of water; mix until easy to spread.
Add baking soda and mix well.
Spread over picante sauce.
Vigorously stir sour cream to make a smoother consistency. Spread over refried beans.

title: sauce bordelaise
directions: Saute diced onions in butter until lightly browned; add flour and mix thoroughly.
Add bouillon; stir until smooth.
Slowly mix in red cooking wine, crushed garlic and chopped parsley.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Prepare vegetables into bite sized pieces.
Keep separate. Heat wok with 1/4 teaspoon oil.
Place onion in pot and stir a few times.
Cover for 1 minute.
Put broccoli and cauliflower into wok and stir frequently; add carrots.
Cover for 2 to 5 minutes until the vegetables are a little cooked.
Add remaining vegetables and stir-fry until mushrooms are moist and noncrunchy.
You want to make sure you do not overcook.
They need to be crisp.
Put Ramen in 3 cups of water with 2 packages Oriental broth.
Steam until noodles start to separate.
Put into small amount of oil and brown.
Add to vegetables and mix.
Add soy sauce to taste.
May add soy sauce to vegetables while cooking.

title: pumpkin pie ice cream(3 pies)
directions: Crush the graham crackers.
Add melted butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon Knox gelatine.
Press warm crumbs into pie pan and chill.

title: blue ribbon teriyaki
directions: Place beef cubes, mushrooms and pineapple chunks alternately onto skewers.
Marinate for 30 minutes in the following sauce and then broil, basting with the sauce.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Press ground round in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onions.
Add Tater Tots.
Pour soup over top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup apple juice.
Combine with remaining juice in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in apple slices; coat well.
Spoon into 9-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle on spices.
Top with remaining pastry.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry pudding (hinds)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat slowly on simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour melted butter over soft bread crumbs and stir into hot blueberries.
Don't crush berries.
Keep warm 1/2 hour but don't cook!
Add a little lemon juice.
Serve with ice cream.

title: apple something
directions: Peel, core and cut apple into 8-inch wedges.
Roll each wedge of apple in a crescent roll (large end first).
Place rolled apple wedges in a greased baking dish size 8 x 8-inch.
Heat water, sugar and margarine until it bubbles.
Pour over rolled apple wedges. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: white bean chicken chili
directions: Cook chicken breasts lightly brown (about 45 minutes). Let chicken cool. When cool, cut in bite size pieces. Put enough broth in soup pot to cover bottom. Saut onions and garlic in it. Add chilies to pot with beans and liquid. Stir well. Mix in cumin, oregano and Tabasco. Add the rest of broth and the chicken. Turn heat up to a slight boil and stir. Turn heat down to medium-low. Cover with a lid and cook for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Shape into small balls. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin pie("mine")
directions: Mix
sugar,
cornstarch,
spices and salt together.
Add eggs to	dry
ingredients.
Stir
into
pumpkin.
Add milk and butter stirring to mix well.
Add vanilla and stir.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° until done.
Dot top with butter.

title: sour cream nut cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour 3 times; mix soda in sour cream.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: rum cake
directions: Boil 2 or 3 minutes.

title: coconut shrimp
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp.
Dry well on paper towels.
Set aside.
In a bowl, mix all dry ingredients for batter.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and ice water.
Stir to blend.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk to the sifted dry ingredients.
Knead dough enough to hold together. Roll dough out to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits with a biscuit cutter and fold in half as a pocket book.
Let biscuits rise for 2 hours if they are left out after the dough is made, 3 hours if they are refrigerated first.
Brush with melted butter or margarine and bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: wally punch
directions: Mix together and serve over ice.
For a less sweet version of this, use grapefruit juice instead of pineapple.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a medium bowl; cut in shortening and butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add sweet potatoes and milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Potatoes can be sliced and cooked in water on top of stove until almost done to cut down on oven time.
Slice potatoes and onions thick.
Add milk to mushroom soup.
Pour layer of potatoes and onions in buttered casserole alternately with soup.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Add paprika, if desired.
Also parsley flakes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and vanilla.
Put in bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: watergate ice cream
directions: Mix pudding, milk and ice cream until stiff.
Mix Ritz crackers, butter and sugar until crumbly.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with crumbs.
Save some crumbs for top.
Pour in pudding mix and add rest of crumbs on top.
Keep in refrigerator until firm.
Can be topped with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and ginger in large bowl.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in carrots, nuts and dates.
Beat eggs and milk together with fork; add to bowl and stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool on rack before slicing.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.

title: veal cutlets parmesan
directions: Dip cutlets in beaten eggs combined with seasonings, then in mixture of Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Fry in butter or oil until brown (about 8 minutes).
Then place cutlets in baking dish. Pour tomato sauce over them and add slices of Mozzarella cheese. Bake in moderate oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: american chowder
directions: Saute onions in margarine. Add potatoes, water, celery and seasonings. Cover and bring to boil. Reduce and simmer 15 minutes until potatoes are done. Gradually add a small amount of milk to flour. Blend. Add flour mixture to hot potatoes. Add remaining milk. Add Smok-Y Links and cheese. Heat through until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.

title: poppy seed cole slaw sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and whip until smooth.
Pour over cabbage and mix.
Remaining sauce can be stored in refrigerator for extended period.
Do not use anything other than "real mayonnaise: or it will be lumpy.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix butter, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Shape in balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: condensed milk
directions: Blend all ingredients together until in blender.
Makes about 14 ounces.
(This is like Eagle Brand milk.)

title: lemon saucelubbock, texas
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and nutmeg; gradually add water, cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Add butter and lemon juice, blend thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pizza dough
directions: Top dough with any of your favorite toppings plus one can pizza sauce.

title: seashell or macaroni soup
directions: Cook in large pot seashells or macaroni.
Add quartered potatoes, then remainder of ingredients.
Let cook until done. Simmer on low heat.
Serve with hot cornbread or crackers.

title: old fashioned egg pie(like my mother used to make)
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, salt, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Slowly stir in hot milk; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Carefully place pie into oven.
Bake in very hot oven (475°) for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Pie will set when completely cooled.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan over medium flame, 10 to 15 minutes, or simmer in crock-pot on high for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat margarine and oil in a Dutch oven or large, heavy saucepan.
Add chicken and brown well.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, bay leaf and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes.
Add rice and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen peas and cook 10 minutes longer or until rice is tender and all the liquid is absorbed.
Has 500 calories per serving.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients, heat until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond curry fruit
directions: All fruits must be well drained.
Place drained fruits in layers in a baking dish; sprinkle with almonds.
Combine melted margarine, brown sugar and curry powder, mixing well; pour this mixture over fruit and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix seasoning and sauce with hamburger.
Add rice.
In a large baking dish, put one layer of rice mixture, one layer of shredded cheese and one layer crushed taco chips.
Keep alternating.
Bake in moderate oven until cheese melts.

title: italian cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Melt butter, then add sugar and eggs. Beat well. Add dry ingredients gradually.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: alhoa chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, celery and almonds or pecans. Add mayonnaise and mix well. Chill. Serve on lettuce and top with pineapple.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease 9-inch square baking dish. Combine first 4 ingredients. Set aside.

Cream butter and eggs. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Alternately add sifted dry ingredients and sour cream to mixture. Pour 1/2 of batter into baking dish. Cover with half of nut topping.
Add remaining batter. Top with remaining nut mixture. Bake approximately 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Slice onion and brown in bacon drippings.
Combine all other ingredients and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix water, orange juice and sugar until boiling.
Put tea and cloves in cloth and leave in mixture 1 minute (or until taste). Now, mix in pineapple juice and serve.
Do not re-boil, only reheat.

title: zucchini bundt cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oil, cinnamon and vanilla for 6 to 7 minutes.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix onion, eggs, mushroom soup and Velveeta cheese in casserole dish.
Cover with crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit pie
directions: Combine and pour in greased Pyrex.
Pour 1 quart fruit over batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's salami
directions: Mix all ingredients good.
Form into 2 logs and roll in foil; twist ends good.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Take out and boil in water 1 hour.
Remove from kettle.
Poke holes in foil to drain. Remove foil and when cooled enough to handle, wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Ready to eat.

title: cheese bites
directions: Spread bread with a layer of the pimento cheese.
Roll bread slices up and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Dip pieces into melted butter and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix and cook until mixture thickens (about 30 minutes). Put in sterile jars and seal immediately.

title: four hour stew
directions: Sprinkle salt, sugar and tapioca over meat.
Add 1 cup tomato juice and crushed garlic.
Put in casserole in layers.
Bake at 250°.
Add potatoes 1 hour before done.
Push potatoes down into juice.

title: linguini with mushroom sauce
directions: Saute in a saucepan: sliced mushrooms, 1/2 diced onion, 1/2 stick butter, garlic to taste and salt to taste, until slightly turning brown.
Meanwhile, cook (boil) linguini in pot with enough water to cover them with a touch of salt.
Add 2 cups of cooking wine to saucepan and bring to a boil, then simmer.
Stir in 1/2 can of tomato paste to turn the sauce to a nice red color.
Cook on low for 3 to 5 minutes.
When linguini is finished cooking, serve with mushroom sauce.

title: puppy chow "for people"
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour over Crispix or Chex cereal.
Coat with powdered sugar.
Lay out flat to dry, about 5 minutes.
Great for the holidays!

title: one step lasagne(here's my favorite heart healthy-vegetarian recipe.)
directions: Defrost and drain spinach.
Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese, spinach, egg and oregano.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Layer starting with 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce; layer of noodles; 1/3 or 1/2 cheese mixture (depending on how many layers you wish to make).
Repeat layering as above.
Top with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Pour 1 cup water over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: sweet pepper conserve
directions: Put peppers through grinder.
Drain liquid and rinse once. Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until thick and jellied.
Pack in sterile jars.
Serve with meat.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Put crackers in large brown paper bag.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over crackers.
Shake bag until thoroughly coated.
Put crackers in bowl or container.
Let stand a short while.
Crackers will appear oily at first, but oily appearance will soon disappear.
Cover and store.

title: peanut butter-fudge cutouts
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with waxed paper.
Combine milk, chips and butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Stir constantly over low heat
until
chips
and
butter
melt and mixture is smooth.
Pour immediately
into
prepared pan.
Spread evenly with wet
metal spatula.
Chill until firm, at least 2 hours. Turn out
onto
flat surface;
peel off waxed paper.
Roll to 1/4-inch
thickness. Cut
in
desired shapes, pressing cookie cutters
firmly into fudge.
Decorate with colored sugars, red cinnamon
candies, silver
dragees,
tubes
of red, white and green decorating gel or whatever you like.

title: black forest chocolate bars
directions: In large bowl, combine all above ingredients. Stir until well blended with a wooden spoon. Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in small amount of oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with onion slices.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, then pour over chops.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes, according to recipe.
I cover with tinfoil and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Boil together the margarine, butter, brown sugar, white sugar and milk.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Add the graham cracker crumbs and boil for another minute.
Line 1 layer of the Waverly crackers in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of the sauce over the crackers.
Next, add another layer of the Waverly crackers and pour the rest of the sauce on top.
Add 1 more layer of the crackers. Melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips along with the peanut butter.
Spread this mixture on top.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix melted margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple goodie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Add all other ingredients in a separate bowl and mix until crumbly.
Pour over apple mixture.
Bake 40 minutes in 375° oven. Serves 6.

title: chicketti
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half; dip in egg.
Roll in crumbs.
In skillet, brown chicken on both sides.
Cover; cook over low heat until tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Spoon a tablespoon of sauce on each chicken piece; top with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.

title: wood chuck
directions: Make a roux of flour and melted butter.
Add milk.
Cook to thicken.
Add cheese and remove from heat.
Stir until cheese melts.
Saute mushrooms and celery in 2 teaspoons butter; add to sauce.
Add turkey or chicken meat (cooked and diced) and 2 hard-boiled eggs (diced).
Serve on plates over the Chinese noodles.
Garnish with slices of the 3rd egg.

title: granny smith apple pie
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar and egg until lumpy.
Crumble over apples. Sprinkle apple pie spice (or cinnamon) over all.
Take 1 stick melted margarine and drizzle over top.
May add pecans.
Bake until crispy.
May add Cool Whip.
(This recipe is from the kitchen of Becky Strain.)

title: chicken in wine
directions: Brown cut up chicken coated with salt, pepper and flour. Remove chicken to 3-quart casserole.
In skillet, add onions, carrots and garlic. Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and Burgundy wine.
Scrape up browned vegetables and simmer all together 2 to 3 minutes.
Dip out solid pieces from skillet and alternate in the casserole in layers with the chicken, adding 2 to 3 sprigs of parsley, 1/4 teaspoon dried thyme, celery leaves and one bay leaf to each layer.
Pour the heated wine over the casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Serve with snipped parsley.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Let cool.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir well.
Add eggs (beat one at a time), flour and nuts.
Stir well.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
After spreading the topping, sprinkle with 1 cup of finely chopped nuts.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix together spinach souffle, eggs, milk, onion, mushrooms and Swiss cheese.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pressed chicken(salad type)
directions: Boil chicken or stewing hen well until meat is done and falls off the bones.
Remove chicken from bones and chop into small pieces.
Use boiled down juice; skim off fat from chicken broth. Add gelatin.
Pour over chicken; mix well and chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in margarine.
Mix other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie shell.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable rice pilaf
directions: Finely chop first 4 ingredients and saute in butter and olive oil.
Set aside.
Add spices and soy sauce.
Cook rice according to directions.
Chop tomatoes and scallions fine.
Rinse and drain pimientos and chop fine.

title: million dollar pickles
directions: Slice pickles.
Make a
brine
of
the boiled water and salt. Let cool.
Put over pickles.
Let stand for 7 days with weight on top.

title: harvey's cole slaw house
directions: Shred cabbage and place in a wide mouth jar or glass dish. Add chopped onions and sugar (and carrots, if desired).

title: broccoli sausage luncheon(serves 4)
directions: Press sausage into the base of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover with sauce, broccoli, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Serve immediately.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Put cake mix
in a large bowl.
Add eggs, orange juice, oil and pudding mix to cake mix in place of ingredients called for on package.
Mix as directed on package. Pour into greased and floured tube cake
pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: quick and easy chicken parmesan
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles.
Cook chicken patties 2 at a time in microwave.
Cover patties while cooking.
Let them stand in microwave 3 minutes.
Heat spaghetti sauce on stove or in microwave.
Then put chicken (with Provolone cheese on top) onto plate.
Put spaghetti noodles beside the chicken and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ground turkey stir-fry
directions: One cup of uncooked kashi may be substituted for brown rice.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Clean and devein shrimp; sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce. Roll in mixture of flour and paprika. Melt butter in large skillet. Add celery, green pepper and onion. Cook over low heat about 5 minutes. Add shrimp; increase heat and cook about 5 minutes more or until flour browns and shrimp turns pink. Add hot rice and a small amount of water, if needed. Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and add with bacon drippings to shrimp. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot.

title: lucy's roast
directions: Place roast in large baking bowl or pan. Pour broth over roast and sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Cover baking dish. Cook roast for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Turn oven heat down to 250° and cook until roast is tender. A large roast will take at least 4 hours. Place carrots and peeled, halved potatoes around roast for the last hour of cooking. Uncover the roast periodically while cooking and ladle broth over meat to keep tender.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and cauliflower until half done (you can steam or boil).
Place florets and stalks in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Layer one can of onion rings on top of vegetables.
Beat together soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with remaining can of onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach orange salad
directions: In large bowl, tear spinach and lettuce into bite-size pieces; add oranges and walnuts.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad and toss to coat.
Cover. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: josh and todd's favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add lemon or vanilla extract and blend well.
Add eggs one at a time and continue beating.
Add baking powder and salt.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt butter, sugar, dates and vanilla in a double boiler. Cook for 10 minutes,
stirring constantly.
Then add remaining ingredients. Let cool. Roll into small balls and shake in confectioners sugar.

title: pop's punch
directions: Mix Sauterne and brandy and chill.
Chill soda water and champagne.
Pour Sauterne-brandy over a block of ice in a punch bowl.
Just before serving, add chilled soda and champagne.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Brown oatmeal, wheat germ, coconut and sesame seed in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well to coat and roast for 5 minutes more.
It's great with yogurt poured over it!

title: super nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown meat and onion; pour off fat.
Add beans, chilies, chili powder, hot pepper sauce and 2 cups shredded cheese spread.
Cook until cheese melts.
Arrange chips on baking sheet.
Top with meat and remaining 2 cups cheese spread.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Garnish as desired.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Mix Ranch dressing and mayonnaise according to directions; chill thoroughly.

title: sally's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 1 cup warm water with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix remaining water and sugar.
Mix with oleo, salt and eggs.
Mix in 4 cups flour.
Mix in yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour.
Knead. Let rise in warm oven.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out 1/2; spread with oleo, brown sugar, and cinnamon.
Cut into small slices.
Put in greased, jelly roll pan.
Repeat with other half. (Should fill 2 jelly roll pans.)
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake.
Ice with powdered sugar glaze.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
In separate bowl, stir together pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Gently stir in topping.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover with heavy-duty foil and freeze.
Slice frozen salad into 3/4-inch slabs and serve on a bed of lettuce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: finger salad
directions: Roll out crescent rolls onto baking sheet.
Bake according to package directions.
Let cool.
Mix dressing, cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Spread onto top of rolls.
Cut into squares.
Place finely chopped vegetables and cheese on top. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: frozen potato casserole
directions: Mix soup and yogurt together.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mealy.
Add yeast to buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Knead lightly.
Roll and cut or refrigerate for later use.
May be kept 8 to 10 days covered in refrigerator.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If rolled thin this can be used as a delicious pizza crust or makes delicious cinnamon rolls.
Spread with melted butter and a mixture of cinnamon and half brown and half white sugar.
Roll in log and cut placing cut side down on greased pan.
Upon removing from oven, immediately cover with glaze of powdered sugar and warm water with a drop or two of almond or vanilla extract.

title: creamy baked mashed potatoes(microwave)
directions: In lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, thoroughly combine all ingredients except cheese.
Microwave on High 7 minutes, turning casserole twice. Top with remaining cheese. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients in large pot for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange frost
directions: Pour orange juice in blender.
Add packet of frost mix and ice.
Blend on high for about 30 seconds.
Makes about 30 to 32 fluid ounces.

title: sugarless apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Peel and cut up apples; add apple juice.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of water.
Stir into apple mixture and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 10 to 15 minutes until apples are done.
Stir in cinnamon.
Dot margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until crust is brown and filling bubbly.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add sauce and cook until hot. Spread small amount of sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cooked noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Swiss cheese; sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Try to have 3 layers.

title: low-fat, low-sugar butterscotch pumpkin pie(for dad)
directions: With whisk in large bowl, beat together until smooth:
cream cheese, 1 tablespoon evaporated skim milk and sugar substitute. Fold in whipped topping.
Spread mixture in bottom of crust.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a 10 inch pie plate, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: doubly good refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed of electric mixer.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 3 minutes with a heavy duty electric mixer at medium speed.
Add yeast mixture and beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for 3 hours or until doubled in bulk.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add soups; mix.
Add rice and water.
Place chicken breasts, dipped in butter, on top of mixture.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: penny saving recipe for "ranch style" salad dressing mix
directions: This recipe makes enough mix for 8 cups of dressing.
Place all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well.
Store in cupboard.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Cream
butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating after each addition. Sift flour, soda and cocoa together. Add alternately with buttermilk, mix well.
Stir in vanilla, coconut
and
pecans.
Fold
in
stiffly
beaten egg whites.
Bake in
greased
layer pans at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hill's baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook for 5 hours on high or 8 hours on low in a crock-pot.
Remove the lid and sit on high for the last hour to thicken beans.
Add hot sauce or peppers for hot beans (to taste).

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Boil celery, potatoes, carrots and onions together in 2 cups water in Dutch oven or large kettle until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except noodles; cook 30 to 60 minutes. The longer it cooks, the better it tastes. Add noodles 15 to 20 minutes before serving. Can be put in hot jars and canned or put in freezer.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic and parsley.
Pour oil all over.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Prick holes in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Uncover and cook an additional 15 minutes. Serves 4.
Buon appetito.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough; gently smooth dough into a ball on floured surface.
Knead 20 times.
Pat dough on bottom and up sides of pan (or roll out on cookie sheet).
Pinch side 3/4 inch edge.
Cook and stir beef, onion, salt and garlic until beef is brown and drain.
Mix tomato sauce and Italian seasoning; spread over dough.
Spread beef over sauce.
Add mushrooms, green peppers and cheese.
Bake until crust browns, 20 minutes.

title: creme brulee
directions: 1. Heat cream and vanilla with half of the sugar until it reaches 170 degrees, simmer.

title: magic marshmallow meltaways
directions: Separate rolls and place one marshmallow in center. Wrap dough all around, pinching closed.
Dip in melted margarine, then roll in cinnamon/sugar. Bake in slightly greased muffin tin at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together peanut butter and margarine.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and place on wax paper.
Let dry.
Melt coating and cool a little.
Dip balls into coating.
Let excess drip off.
Place on wax paper.
Makes about 25.

title: alaskan sheet cake
directions: Boil water and margarine.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add first mixture.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix, then cover with cracker crumbs and pour over 1/4 cup butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: macadamia nut chiffon pie
directions: Mix gelatin, sugar and salt.
Beat together egg yolks, cold milk and water.
Stir into gelatin mixture and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold nuts and whipped cream into mixture and add vanilla.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Then top with additional whipped cream and sprinkle with Macadamia nuts.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Heat to boiling point milk and 1 tablespoon butter.
Add at once to mixture.
Beat well. Do not add any more flour, the batter is very thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and spread with blended mixture of melted butter, brown sugar and cream.

title: fruit tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add enough water to make a gallon.

title: betty's pink shower punch(makes thirty 7 ounce cups)
directions: Serve with floating ring of ice.
To make other flavors (colors), substitute other flavors Kool-Aid and sherbet.

title: dilled carrots
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until carrots are tender (about 15 minutes).
Drain.
Add yogurt and dill; heat briefly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla and spoon on top of crust.
Lay bananas on top.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Spread pineapple on top.
Pecans and cherries may be added, if desired.

title: no roll pastry shell
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pie pan.
Combine milk and oil in cup.
Whip with fork and pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix until flour is completely dampened.
Press evenly with fingers to line bottom of pan and up the sides.
Be sure dough is pressed to uniform thickness.
To flute:
Prick entire surface.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
For unbaked shell:
Fill as desired and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: sunshine pasta salad
directions: Mix all together except pineapple and broccoli.
Cover, chill and toss together just before serving.
Makes 20 cups.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish with skin side up.
Pour cans of soup over chicken. Add dash of salt and pepper on top of each chicken breast.
Pour both wines over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Use liquid to make gravy.

title: seared pork loin and blackberries
directions: Place sugar, 2 tablespoons butter, vinegar and onions in heavy skillet over medium-low heat.
Stir to coat well.
Cook uncovered 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix other ingredients together in separate bowl and combine the 2 mixtures.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beignets(kind of like elephant ears)
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening, then add the cream. Let mixture stand until warm (not hot). Separately sprinkle yeast over warm water in a bowl. Let stand until dissolved, then add shortening mixture. Mix well. Add 2 cups of flour and eggs; beat until well combined. Add just enough of remaining flour to make dough soft and not sticky. Put dough on lightly floured surface. Pat into rectangle, about 1-inch thick. Use rolling pin to roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Heat oil to 360° in large skillet or pot.
Fry to crispy brown on all sides. Drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar. Best right away.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine drained pineapple, mandarin oranges and cottage cheese.
Put dry jello over mixture and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip and put in bowl.
Chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, minced onion, dill weed and mayonnaise.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crescent rolls.
Sprinkle your choice of fresh vegetables over cream cheese.
Press in lightly.

title: syllabub
directions: Beat together until sugar is dissolved and mixture is frothy. Serve immediately.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: zesty salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; cool for 1 hour before serving.

title: pickled squash
directions: Slice squash and onions thin.
Cover with water.
Add salt and let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix spices and sugar, then add vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add squash and onions and let stand 2 hours.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars.
They seal by themselves.

title: crabbies
directions: Split muffins.
Mix other ingredients
and spread on 12 muffin halves.
Cut each muffin half into sixths.
Broil until bubbly. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Mix with mayonnaise, eggs, flour and milk.
Mix in crab meat and half of cheese.
Pour into pie crust and put remaining cheese on top of quiche.
You can make your own pie crust or buy one.
Bake in crust for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: silver cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream shortening with the sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add the dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Pour into 3 greased 8-inch round pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon french bread
directions: Combine lemon rind and garlic powder with margarine.
Spread on bread and toast until lightly browned.
